{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"1KI"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["1 Kings \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The First Book of Kings \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["1 Kings \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["1Ki \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["The First Book of Kings \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"1KI 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 1:1"},"Now king Dawood was old and advanced in years; and they covered him with clothes, but he couldn’t keep warm.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 1:2"},"Therefore his servants said to him, “Let a young virgin be sought for my lord the king. Let her stand before the king, and\ncherish him; and let her lie in your bosom, that my lord the king may keep warm.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 1:3"},"So they sought for a beautiful young lady throughout all the borders of Israel, and found Abishag the Shunammite, and\nbrought her to the king. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 1:4"},"The young lady was very beautiful; and she cherished the king, and served him; but the king didn’t know her intimately.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 1:5"},"Then Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, “I will be king.” Then he prepared him chariots and horsemen,\nand fifty men to run before him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 1:6"},"His father had not displeased him at any time in saying, “Why have you done so?” and he was also a very handsome man; and\nhe was born after Absalom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 1:7"},"He conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah, and with Abiathar the priest; and they followed Adonijah and helped him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 1:8"},"But Zadok the priest, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, Nathan the prophet, Shimei, Rei, and the mighty men who belonged to\nDawood, were not with Adonijah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 1:9"},"Adonijah killed sheep, cattle, and fatlings by the stone of Zoheleth, which is beside En Rogel; and he called all his\nbrothers, the king’s sons, and all the men of Judah, the king’s servants;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 1:10"},"but he didn’t call Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah, and the mighty men, and Sulaiman his brother.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 1:11"},"Then Nathan spoke to Bathsheba the mother of Sulaiman, saying, “Haven’t you heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith\nreigns, and Dawood our lord doesn’t know it? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 1:12"},"Now therefore come, please let me give you counsel, that you may save your own life, and your son Sulaiman’s life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 1:13"},"Go in to king Dawood, and tell him, ‘Didn’t you, my lord, king, swear to your servant, saying, “Assuredly Sulaiman your\nson shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne?” Why then does Adonijah reign?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 1:14"},"Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," while you are still talking there with the king, I will also come in after you and confirm your words.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 1:15"},"Bathsheba went in to the king in his room. The king was very old; and Abishag the Shunammite was serving the king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 1:16"},"Bathsheba bowed, and showed respect to the king. The king said, “What would you like?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 1:17"},"She said to him, “My lord, you swore by the LORD",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:17\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper Name.\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," your Allah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים”\n(Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"}," to your servant, ‘Assuredly Sulaiman your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 1:18"},"Now, behold, Adonijah reigns; and you, my lord the king, don’t know it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 1:19"},"He has slain cattle and fatlings and sheep in abundance, and has called all the sons of the king, Abiathar the priest,\nand Joab the captain of the army; but he hasn’t called Sulaiman your servant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 1:20"},"You, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, that you should tell them who will sit on the throne of my lord\nthe king after him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 1:21"},"Otherwise it will happen, when my lord the king sleeps with his fathers, that I and my son Sulaiman will be considered\ncriminals.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 1:22"},"Behold, while she was still talking with the king, Nathan the prophet came in.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 1:23"},"They told the king, saying, “Behold, Nathan the prophet!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When he had come in before the king, he bowed himself before the king with his face to the ground.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 1:24"},"Nathan said, “My lord, king, have you said, ‘Adonijah shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 1:25"},"For he has gone down today, and has slain cattle, fatlings, and sheep in abundance, and has called all the king’s sons,\nthe captains of the army, and Abiathar the priest. Behold, they are eating and drinking before him, and saying, ‘Long live king\nAdonijah!’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 1:26"},"But he hasn’t called me, even me your servant, Zadok the priest, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and your servant Sulaiman.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 1:27"},"Was this thing done by my lord the king, and you haven’t shown to your servants who should sit on the throne of my lord\nthe king after him?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 1:28"},"Then king Dawood answered, “Call Bathsheba in to me.” She came into the king’s presence and stood before the king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 1:29"},"The king swore, and said, “As the LORD lives, who has redeemed my soul out of all adversity,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 1:30"},"most certainly as I swore to you by the LORD, Allah of Israel, saying, ‘Assuredly Sulaiman your son shall reign after me,\nand he shall sit on my throne in my place;’ I will most certainly do this today.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 1:31"},"Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the earth, and showed respect to the king, and said, “Let my lord king Dawood live\nforever!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 1:32"},"King Dawood said, “Call to me Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada.” They came before\nthe king. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 1:33"},"The king said to them, “Take with you the servants of your lord, and cause Sulaiman my son to ride on my own mule, and\nbring him down to Gihon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 1:34"},"Let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint him there king over Israel. Blow the trumpet, and say, ‘Long live king\nSulaiman!’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 1:35"},"Then come up after him, and he shall come and sit on my throne; for he shall be king in my place. I have appointed him to\nbe prince over Israel and over Judah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 1:36"},"Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king, and said, “Amen. May the LORD, Allah of my lord the king, say so.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 1:37"},"As the LORD has been with my lord the king, even so may he be with Sulaiman, and make his throne greater than the throne\nof my lord king Dawood.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 1:38"},"So Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites and the Pelethites went down\nand had Sulaiman ride on king Dawood’s mule, and brought him to Gihon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 1:39"},"Zadok the priest took the horn of oil from the Tent, and anointed Sulaiman. They blew the trumpet; and all the people\nsaid, “Long live king Sulaiman!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 1:40"},"All the people came up after him, and the people piped with pipes, and rejoiced with great joy, so that the earth shook\nwith their sound. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 1:41"},"Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they had finished eating. When Joab heard the sound of the\ntrumpet, he said, “Why is this noise of the city being in an uproar?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 1:42"},"While he yet spoke, behold, Jonathan the son of Abiathar the priest came; and Adonijah said, “Come in; for you are a\nworthy man, and bring good news.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 1:43"},"Jonathan answered Adonijah, “Most certainly our lord king Dawood has made Sulaiman king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"1KI 1:44"},"The king has sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites and the\nPelethites; and they have caused him to ride on the king’s mule.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"1KI 1:45"},"Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king in Gihon. They have come up from there rejoicing, so that\nthe city rang again. This is the noise that you have heard. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"1KI 1:46"},"Also, Sulaiman sits on the throne of the kingdom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"1KI 1:47"},"Moreover the king’s servants came to bless our lord king Dawood, saying, ‘May your Allah make the name of Sulaiman better\nthan your name, and make his throne greater than your throne;’ and the king bowed himself on the bed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"1KI 1:48"},"Also thus said the king, ‘Blessed be the LORD, Allah of Israel, who has given one to sit on my throne today, my eyes even\nseeing it.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"1KI 1:49"},"All the guests of Adonijah were afraid, and rose up, and each man went his way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"1KI 1:50"},"Adonijah was afraid because of Sulaiman; and he arose, and went, and hung onto the horns of the altar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"1KI 1:51"},"Sulaiman was told, “Behold, Adonijah fears king Sulaiman; for, behold, he is hanging onto the horns of the altar, saying,\n‘Let king Sulaiman swear to me first that he will not kill his servant with the sword.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"1KI 1:52"},"Sulaiman said, “If he shows himself a worthy man, not a hair of his shall fall to the earth; but if wickedness is found\nin him, he shall die.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"1KI 1:53"},"So king Sulaiman sent, and they brought him down from the altar. He came and bowed down to king Sulaiman; and Sulaiman\nsaid to him, “Go to your house.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"1KI 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 2:1"},"Now the days of Dawood came near that he should die; and he commanded Sulaiman his son, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 2:2"},"“I am going the way of all the earth. You be strong therefore, and show yourself a man;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 2:3"},"and keep the instruction of Allah your LORD, to walk in his ways, to keep his statutes, his commandments, his ordinances,\nand his testimonies, according to that which is written in the law of Musa, that you may prosper in all that you do, and\nwherever you turn yourself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 2:4"},"Then the LORD may establish his word which he spoke concerning me, saying, ‘If your children are careful of their way, to\nwalk before me in truth with all their heart and with all their soul, there shall not fail you,’ he said, ‘a man on the throne\nof Israel.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 2:5"},"“Moreover you know also what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to me, even what he did to the two captains of the armies of\nIsrael, to Abner the son of Ner, and to Amasa the son of Jether, whom he killed, and shed the blood of war in peace, and put\nthe blood of war on his sash that was around his waist, and in his sandals that were on his feet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 2:6"},"Do therefore according to your wisdom, and don’t let his grey head go down to\nSheol",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}],"caller":"+"}," in peace.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 2:7"},"But show kindness to the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let them be amongst those who eat at your table; for so they\ncame to me when I fled from Absalom your brother. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 2:8"},"“Behold, there is with you Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjamite, of Bahurim, who cursed me with a grievous curse in the\nday when I went to Mahanaim; but he came down to meet me at the Jordan, and I swore to him by the LORD, saying, ‘I will not put\nyou to death with the sword.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 2:9"},"Now therefore don’t hold him guiltless, for you are a wise man; and you will know what you ought to do to him, and you\nshall bring his grey head down to Sheol",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}],"caller":"+"}," with blood.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 2:10"},"Dawood slept with his fathers, and was buried in Dawood’s city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 2:11"},"The days that Dawood reigned over Israel were forty years; he reigned seven years in Hebron, and he reigned thirty-three\nyears in Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 2:12"},"Sulaiman sat on Dawood his father’s throne; and his kingdom was firmly established.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 2:13"},"Then Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Sulaiman. She said, “Do you come peaceably?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Peaceably. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 2:14"},"He said moreover, I have something to tell you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She said, “Say on.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 2:15"},"He said, “You know that the kingdom was mine, and that all Israel set their faces on me, that I should reign. However the\nkingdom is turned around, and has become my brother’s; for it was his from the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 2:16"},"Now I ask one petition of you. Don’t deny me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She said to him, “Say on.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 2:17"},"He said, “Please speak to Sulaiman the king (for he will not tell you ‘no’), that he give me Abishag the Shunammite as\nwife.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 2:18"},"Bathsheba said, “All right. I will speak for you to the king.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 2:19"},"Bathsheba therefore went to king Sulaiman, to speak to him for Adonijah. The king rose up to meet her, and bowed himself\nto her, and sat down on his throne, and caused a throne to be set for the king’s mother; and she sat on his right hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 2:20"},"Then she said, “I ask one small petition of you; don’t deny me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The king said to her, “Ask on, my mother; for I will not deny you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 2:21"},"She said, “Let Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah your brother as wife.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 2:22"},"King Sulaiman answered his mother, “Why do you ask Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? Ask for him the kingdom also; for\nhe is my elder brother; even for him, and for Abiathar the priest, and for Joab the son of Zeruiah.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 2:23"},"Then king Sulaiman swore by the LORD, saying, “Allah do so to me, and more also, if Adonijah has not spoken this word\nagainst his own life. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 2:24"},"Now therefore as the LORD lives, who has established me, and set me on my father Dawood’s throne, and who has made me a\nhouse as he promised, surely Adonijah shall be put to death today.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 2:25"},"King Sulaiman sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; and he fell on him, so that he died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 2:26"},"To Abiathar the priest the king said, “Go to Anathoth, to your own fields; for you are worthy of death. But I will not at\nthis time put you to death, because you bore the Lord",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:26\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word translated “Lord” is “Adonai.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ALLAH’s ark before Dawood my father, and because you were afflicted in all in\nwhich my father was afflicted.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 2:27"},"So Sulaiman thrust Abiathar out from being priest to the LORD, that he might fulfil the LORD’s word, which he spoke\nconcerning the house of Eli in Shiloh. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 2:28"},"This news came to Joab; for Joab had followed Adonijah, although he didn’t follow Absalom. Joab fled to the LORD’s Tent,\nand held onto the horns of the altar. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 2:29"},"King Sulaiman was told, “Joab has fled to the LORD’s Tent, and behold, he is by the altar.” Then Sulaiman sent Benaiah\nthe son of Jehoiada, saying, “Go, fall on him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 2:30"},"Benaiah came to the LORD’s Tent, and said to him, “The king says, ‘Come out!’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “No; but I will die here.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Benaiah brought the king word again, saying, “This is what Joab said, and this is how he answered me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 2:31"},"The king said to him, “Do as he has said, and fall on him, and bury him; that you may take away the blood, which Joab\nshed without cause, from me and from my father’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 2:32"},"The LORD will return his blood on his own head, because he fell on two men more righteous and better than he, and killed\nthem with the sword, and my father Dawood didn’t know it: Abner the son of Ner, captain of the army of Israel, and Amasa the\nson of Jether, captain of the army of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 2:33"},"So their blood will return on the head of Joab, and on the head of his\noffspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," forever. But for Dawood, for his offspring, for his house, and for his throne, there\nwill be peace forever from the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 2:34"},"Then Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up and fell on him, and killed him; and he was buried in his own house in the\nwilderness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 2:35"},"The king put Benaiah the son of Jehoiada in his place over the army; and the king put Zadok the priest in the place of\nAbiathar. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 2:36"},"The king sent and called for Shimei, and said to him, “Build yourself a house in Jerusalem, and live there, and don’t go\nanywhere else. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 2:37"},"For on the day you go out and pass over the brook Kidron, know for certain that you will surely die. Your blood will be\non your own head.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 2:38"},"Shimei said to the king, “What you say is good. As my lord the king has said, so will your servant do.” Shimei lived in\nJerusalem many days. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 2:39"},"At the end of three years, two of Shimei’s slaves ran away to Achish, son of Maacah, king of Gath. They told Shimei,\nsaying, “Behold, your slaves are in Gath.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 2:40"},"Shimei arose, saddled his donkey, and went to Gath to Achish, to seek his slaves; and Shimei went, and brought his slaves\nfrom Gath. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 2:41"},"Sulaiman was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath, and had come again.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 2:42"},"The king sent and called for Shimei, and said to him, “Didn’t I adjure you by the LORD, and warn you, saying, ‘Know for\ncertain, that on the day you go out, and walk anywhere else, you shall surely die?’ You said to me, ‘The saying that I have\nheard is good.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 2:43"},"Why then have you not kept the oath of the LORD, and the commandment that I have instructed you with?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"1KI 2:44"},"The king said moreover to Shimei, “You know in your heart all the wickedness that you did to Dawood my father. Therefore\nthe LORD will return your wickedness on your own head. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"1KI 2:45"},"But king Sulaiman will be blessed, and Dawood’s throne will be established before the LORD forever.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"1KI 2:46"},"So the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; and he went out, and fell on him, so that he died. The kingdom was\nestablished in the hand of Sulaiman. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"1KI 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 3:1"},"Sulaiman made an alliance with Pharaoh king of Egypt, and took Pharaoh’s daughter, and brought her into Dawood’s city,\nuntil he had finished building his own house, the LORD’s house, and the wall around Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 3:2"},"However the people sacrificed in the high places, because there was not yet a house built for the LORD’s name.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 3:3"},"Sulaiman loved the LORD, walking in the statutes of Dawood his father; except that he sacrificed and burnt incense in the\nhigh places. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 3:4"},"The king went to Gibeon to sacrifice there; for that was the great high place. Sulaiman offered a thousand burnt offerings\non that altar. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 3:5"},"In Gibeon, the LORD appeared to Sulaiman in a dream by night; and Allah said, “Ask for what I should give you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 3:6"},"Sulaiman said, “You have shown to your servant Dawood my father great loving kindness, because he walked before you in\ntruth, in righteousness, and in uprightness of heart with you. You have kept for him this great loving kindness, that you have\ngiven him a son to sit on his throne, as it is today. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 3:7"},"Now, LORD my Allah, you have made your servant king instead of Dawood my father. I am just a little child. I don’t know\nhow to go out or come in. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 3:8"},"Your servant is amongst your people which you have chosen, a great people, that can’t be numbered or counted for\nmultitude. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 3:9"},"Give your servant therefore an understanding heart to judge your people, that I may discern between good and evil; for who\nis able to judge this great people of yours?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 3:10"},"This request pleased the Lord, that Sulaiman had asked this thing.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 3:11"},"Allah said to him, “Because you have asked this thing, and have not asked for yourself long life, nor have you asked for\nriches for yourself, nor have you asked for the life of your enemies, but have asked for yourself understanding to discern\njustice; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 3:12"},"behold, I have done according to your word. Behold, I have given you a wise and understanding heart; so that there has\nbeen no one like you before you, and after you none will arise like you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 3:13"},"I have also given you that which you have not asked, both riches and honour, so that there will not be any amongst the\nkings like you for all your days. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 3:14"},"If you will walk in my ways, to keep my statutes and my commandments, as your father Dawood walked, then I will lengthen\nyour days.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 3:15"},"Sulaiman awoke; and behold, it was a dream. Then he came to Jerusalem, and stood before the ark of the LORD’s covenant,\nand offered up burnt offerings, offered peace offerings, and made a feast for all his servants.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 3:16"},"Then two women who were prostitutes came to the king, and stood before him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 3:17"},"The one woman said, “Oh, my lord, I and this woman dwell in one house. I delivered a child with her in the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 3:18"},"The third day after I delivered, this woman delivered also. We were together. There was no stranger with us in the house,\njust us two in the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 3:19"},"This woman’s child died in the night, because she lay on it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 3:20"},"She arose at midnight, and took my son from beside me, while your servant slept, and laid it in her bosom, and laid her\ndead child in my bosom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 3:21"},"When I rose in the morning to nurse my child, behold, it was dead; but when I had looked at it in the morning, behold, it\nwas not my son, whom I bore.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 3:22"},"The other woman said, “No; but the living one is my son, and the dead one is your son.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The first one said, “No; but the dead one is your son, and the living one is my son.” They argued like this before the king.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 3:23"},"Then the king said, “One says, ‘This is my son who lives, and your son is the dead;’ and the other says, ‘No; but your\nson is the dead one, and my son is the living one.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 3:24"},"The king said, “Get me a sword.” So they brought a sword before the king.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 3:25"},"The king said, “Divide the living child in two, and give half to the one, and half to the other.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 3:26"},"Then the woman whose the living child was spoke to the king, for her heart yearned over her son, and she said, “Oh, my\nlord, give her the living child, and in no way kill him!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But the other said, “He shall be neither mine nor yours. Divide him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 3:27"},"Then the king answered, “Give her the living child, and definitely do not kill him. She is his mother.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 3:28"},"All Israel heard of the judgement which the king had judged; and they feared the king; for they saw that the wisdom of\nAllah was in him, to do justice. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"1KI 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 4:1"},"King Sulaiman was king over all Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 4:2"},"These were the princes whom he had: Azariah the son of Zadok, the priest;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 4:3"},"Elihoreph and Ahijah, the sons of Shisha, scribes; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud, the recorder;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 4:4"},"Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the army; Zadok and Abiathar were priests;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 4:5"},"Azariah the son of Nathan was over the officers; Zabud the son of Nathan was chief minister, the king’s friend;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 4:6"},"Ahishar was over the household; and Adoniram the son of Abda was over the men subject to forced labour.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 4:7"},"Sulaiman had twelve officers over all Israel, who provided food for the king and his household. Each man had to make\nprovision for a month in the year. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 4:8"},"These are their names: Ben Hur, in the hill country of Ephraim;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 4:9"},"Ben Deker, in Makaz, in Shaalbim, Beth Shemesh, and Elon Beth Hanan;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 4:10"},"Ben Hesed, in Arubboth (Socoh and all the land of Hepher belonged to him);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 4:11"},"Ben Abinadab, in all the height of Dor (he had Taphath, Sulaiman’s daughter, as wife);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 4:12"},"Baana the son of Ahilud, in Taanach and Megiddo, and all Beth Shean which is beside Zarethan, beneath Jezreel, from Beth\nShean to Habil Meholah, as far as beyond Jokmeam; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 4:13"},"Ben Geber, in Ramoth Gilead (the towns of Jair the son of Manasseh, which are in Gilead, belonged to him; and the region\nof Argob, which is in Bashan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars, belonged to him);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 4:14"},"Ahinadab the son of Iddo, in Mahanaim; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 4:15"},"Ahimaaz, in Naphtali (he also took Basemath the daughter of Sulaiman as wife);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 4:16"},"Baana the son of Hushai, in Asher and Bealoth; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 4:17"},"Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 4:18"},"Shimei the son of Ela, in Benjamin; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 4:19"},"Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, the country of Sihon king of the Amorites and of Og king of Bashan; and he\nwas the only officer who was in the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 4:20"},"Judah and Israel were numerous as the sand which is by the sea in multitude, eating and drinking and making merry.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 4:21"},"Sulaiman ruled over all the kingdoms from the River to the land of the Philistines, and to the border of Egypt. They\nbrought tribute and served Sulaiman all the days of his life. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 4:22"},"Sulaiman’s provision for one day was thirty cors",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:22\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 cor is the same as a homer, or about 55.9 U. S. gallons (liquid) or 211 litres or 6\nbushels"]}],"caller":"+"}," of fine flour, sixty measures of meal, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 4:23"},"ten head of fat cattle, twenty head of cattle out of the pastures, and one hundred sheep, in addition to deer, and\ngazelles, and roebucks, and fattened fowl. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 4:24"},"For he had dominion over all on this side the River, from Tiphsah even to Gaza, over all the kings on this side the\nRiver: and he had peace on all sides around him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 4:25"},"Judah and Israel lived safely, every man under his vine and under his fig tree, from Dan even to Beersheba, all the days\nof Sulaiman. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 4:26"},"Sulaiman had forty thousand stalls of horses for his chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 4:27"},"Those officers provided food for king Sulaiman, and for all who came to king Sulaiman’s table, every man in his month.\nThey let nothing be lacking. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 4:28"},"They also brought Barley and straw for the horses and swift steeds to the place where the officers were, each man\naccording to his duty. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 4:29"},"Allah gave Sulaiman abundant wisdom and understanding, and very great understanding, even as the sand that is on the\nseashore. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 4:30"},"Sulaiman’s wisdom excelled the wisdom of all the children of the east and all the wisdom of Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 4:31"},"For he was wiser than all men; than Ethan the Ezrahite, Heman, Calcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol: and his fame was in\nall the nations all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 4:32"},"He spoke three thousand proverbs; and his songs numbered one thousand and five.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 4:33"},"He spoke of trees, from the cedar that is in Lebanon even to the hyssop that grows out of the wall; he also spoke of\nanimals, of birds, of creeping things, and of fish. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 4:34"},"People of all nations came to hear the wisdom of Sulaiman, sent by all kings of the earth, who had heard of his wisdom.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"1KI 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 5:1"},"Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Sulaiman; for he had heard that they had anointed him king in the place of his\nfather, and Hiram had always loved Dawood. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 5:2"},"Sulaiman sent to Hiram, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 5:3"},"“You know that Dawood my father could not build a house for the name of the LORD his Allah because of the wars which were\naround him on every side, until the LORD put his enemies under the soles of his feet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 5:4"},"But now the LORD my Allah has given me rest on every side. There is no enemy and no evil occurrence.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 5:5"},"Behold, I intend to build a house for the name of the LORD my Allah, as the LORD spoke to Dawood my father, saying, ‘Your\nson, whom I will set on your throne in your place shall build the house for my name.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 5:6"},"Now therefore command that cedar trees be cut for me out of Lebanon. My servants will be with your servants; and I will\ngive you wages for your servants according to all that you say. For you know that there is nobody amongst us who knows how to\ncut timber like the Sidonians.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 5:7"},"When Hiram heard the words of Sulaiman, he rejoiced greatly, and said, “Blessed is the LORD today, who has given to Dawood\na wise son to rule over this great people.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 5:8"},"Hiram sent to Sulaiman, saying, “I have heard the message which you have sent to me. I will do all your desire concerning\ntimber of cedar, and concerning cypress timber. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 5:9"},"My servants will bring them down from Lebanon to the sea. I will make them into rafts to go by sea to the place that you\nspecify to me, and will cause them to be broken up there, and you will receive them. You will accomplish my desire, in giving\nfood for my household.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 5:10"},"So Hiram gave Sulaiman cedar timber and cypress timber according to all his desire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 5:11"},"Sulaiman gave Hiram twenty thousand cors",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["20,000 cors would be about 120,000 bushels or about 4.2\nmegalitres of wheat, which would weigh about 3,270 metric tonnes."]}],"caller":"+"}," of wheat for food to his household, and twenty\ncors",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["20 cors is about 1,100 gallons or about 4220\nlitres."]}],"caller":"+"}," of pure oil. Sulaiman gave this to Hiram year by year.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 5:12"},"The LORD gave Sulaiman wisdom, as he promised him. There was peace between Hiram and Sulaiman, and the two of them made a\ntreaty together. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 5:13"},"King Sulaiman raised a levy out of all Israel; and the levy was thirty thousand men.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 5:14"},"He sent them to Lebanon, ten thousand a month by courses; for a month they were in Lebanon, and two months at home; and\nAdoniram was over the men subject to forced labour. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 5:15"},"Sulaiman had seventy thousand who bore burdens, and eighty thousand who were stone cutters in the mountains;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 5:16"},"besides Sulaiman’s chief officers who were over the work, three thousand and three hundred, who ruled over the people who\nlaboured in the work. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 5:17"},"The king commanded, and they cut out large stones, costly stones, to lay the foundation of the house with worked stone.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 5:18"},"Sulaiman’s builders and Hiram’s builders and the Gebalites cut them, and prepared the timber and the stones to build the\nhouse. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"1KI 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 6:1"},"In the four hundred and eightieth year after the children of Israel had come out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year\nof Sulaiman’s reign over Israel, in the month Ziv, which is the second month, he began to build the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 6:2"},"The house which king Sulaiman built for the LORD had a length of sixty\ncubits,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," and its width twenty, and its height thirty cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 6:3"},"The porch in front of the temple of the house had a length of twenty cubits, which was along the width of the house. Ten\ncubits was its width in front of the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 6:4"},"He made windows of fixed lattice work for the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 6:5"},"Against the wall of the house, he built floors all around, against the walls of the house all around, both of the temple\nand of the inner sanctuary; and he made side rooms all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 6:6"},"The lowest floor was five cubits wide, and the middle was six cubits wide, and the third was seven cubits wide; for on the\noutside he made offsets in the wall of the house all around, that the beams should not be inserted into the walls of the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 6:7"},"The house, when it was under construction, was built of stone prepared at the quarry; and no hammer or axe or any tool of\niron was heard in the house while it was under construction. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 6:8"},"The door for the middle side rooms was in the right side of the house. They went up by winding stairs into the middle\nfloor, and out of the middle into the third. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 6:9"},"So he built the house, and finished it; and he covered the house with beams and planks of cedar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 6:10"},"He built the floors all along the house, each five cubits high; and they rested on the house with timber of cedar.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 6:11"},"The LORD’s word came to Sulaiman, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 6:12"},"“Concerning this house which you are building, if you will walk in my statutes, and execute my ordinances, and keep all\nmy commandments to walk in them; then I will establish my word with you, which I spoke to Dawood your father.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 6:13"},"I will dwell amongst the children of Israel, and will not forsake my people Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 6:14"},"So Sulaiman built the house, and finished it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 6:15"},"He built the walls of the house within with boards of cedar: from the floor of the house to the walls of the ceiling, he\ncovered them on the inside with wood; and he covered the floor of the house with cypress boards.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 6:16"},"He built twenty cubits on the back part of the house with boards of cedar from the floor to the ceiling. He built them\nfor it within, for an inner sanctuary, even for the most holy place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 6:17"},"In front of the temple sanctuary was forty cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 6:18"},"There was cedar on the house within, carved with buds and open flowers. All was cedar. No stone was visible.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 6:19"},"He prepared an inner sanctuary in the middle of the house within, to set the ark of the LORD’s covenant there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 6:20"},"Within the inner sanctuary was twenty cubits in length, and twenty cubits in width, and twenty cubits in its height; and\nhe overlaid it with pure gold; and he covered the altar with cedar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 6:21"},"So Sulaiman overlaid the house within with pure gold. He drew chains of gold across before the inner sanctuary, and he\noverlaid it with gold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 6:22"},"He overlaid the whole house with gold, until all the house was finished. He also overlaid the whole altar that belonged\nto the inner sanctuary with gold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 6:23"},"In the inner sanctuary he made two cherubim",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Cherubim” is plural of “cherub”, an angelic\nbeing."]}],"caller":"+"}," of olive wood, each ten cubits high. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 6:24"},"Five cubits was the one wing of the cherub, and five cubits the other wing of the cherub. From the tip of one wing to the\ntip of the other was ten cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 6:25"},"The other cherub was ten cubits. Both the cherubim were of one measure and one form.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 6:26"},"One cherub was ten cubits high, and so was the other cherub.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 6:27"},"He set the cherubim within the inner house. The wings of the cherubim were stretched out, so that the wing of the one\ntouched the one wall, and the wing of the other cherub touched the other wall; and their wings touched one another in the\nmiddle of the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 6:28"},"He overlaid the cherubim with gold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 6:29"},"He carved all the walls of the house around with carved figures of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers, inside and\noutside. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 6:30"},"He overlaid the floor of the house with gold, inside and outside.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 6:31"},"For the entrance of the inner sanctuary, he made doors of olive wood. The lintel and door posts were a fifth part of the\nwall. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 6:32"},"So he made two doors of olive wood; and he carved on them carvings of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers, and\noverlaid them with gold. He spread the gold on the cherubim and on the palm trees.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 6:33"},"He also did so for the entrance of the temple door posts of olive wood, out of a fourth part of the wall;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 6:34"},"and two doors of cypress wood. The two leaves of the one door were folding, and the two leaves of the other door were\nfolding. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 6:35"},"He carved cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers; and he overlaid them with gold fitted on the engraved work.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 6:36"},"He built the inner court with three courses of cut stone and a course of cedar beams.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 6:37"},"The foundation of the LORD’s house was laid in the fourth year, in the month Ziv.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 6:38"},"In the eleventh year, in the month Bul, which is the eighth month, the house was finished throughout all its parts, and\naccording to all its specifications. So he spent seven years building it.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"1KI 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 7:1"},"Sulaiman was building his own house thirteen years, and he finished all his house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 7:2"},"For he built the House of the Forest of Lebanon. Its length was one hundred\ncubits,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," its width fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits, on four rows of cedar pillars, with cedar\nbeams on the pillars. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 7:3"},"It was covered with cedar above over the forty-five beams, that were on the pillars, fifteen in a row.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 7:4"},"There were beams in three rows, and window was facing window in three ranks.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 7:5"},"All the doors and posts were made square with beams: and window was facing window in three ranks.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 7:6"},"He made the porch of pillars. Its length was fifty cubits and its width thirty cubits; with a porch before them, and\npillars and a threshold before them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 7:7"},"He made the porch of the throne where he was to judge, even the porch of judgement; and it was covered with cedar from\nfloor to floor. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 7:8"},"His house where he was to dwell, the other court within the porch, was of the like work. He made also a house for\nPharaoh’s daughter (whom Sulaiman had taken as wife), like this porch.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 7:9"},"All these were of costly stones, even of cut stone, according to measure, sawed with saws, inside and outside, even from\nthe foundation to the coping, and so on the outside to the great court.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 7:10"},"The foundation was of costly stones, even great stones, stones of ten cubits, and stones of eight cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 7:11"},"Above were costly stones, even cut stone, according to measure, and cedar wood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 7:12"},"The great court around had three courses of cut stone, and a course of cedar beams; like the inner court of the LORD’s\nhouse and the porch of the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 7:13"},"King Sulaiman sent and brought Hiram out of Tyre. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 7:14"},"He was the son of a widow of the tribe of Naphtali, and his father was a man of Tyre, a worker in bronze; and he was\nfilled with wisdom and understanding and skill, to work all works in bronze. He came to king Sulaiman, and performed all his\nwork. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 7:15"},"For he fashioned the two pillars of bronze, eighteen cubits high apiece; and a line of twelve cubits encircled either of\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 7:16"},"He made two capitals of molten bronze, to set on the tops of the pillars. The height of the one capital was five cubits,\nand the height of the other capital was five cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 7:17"},"There were nets of checker work, and wreaths of chain work, for the capitals which were on the top of the pillars; seven\nfor the one capital, and seven for the other capital. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 7:18"},"So he made the pillars; and there were two rows around on the one network, to cover the capitals that were on the top of\nthe pillars: and he did so for the other capital. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 7:19"},"The capitals that were on the top of the pillars in the porch were of lily work, four cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 7:20"},"There were capitals above also on the two pillars, close by the belly which was beside the network. There were two\nhundred pomegranates in rows around the other capital. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 7:21"},"He set up the pillars at the porch of the temple. He set up the right pillar, and called its name Jachin; and he set up\nthe left pillar, and called its name Boaz. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 7:22"},"On the top of the pillars was lily work: so the work of the pillars was finished.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 7:23"},"He made the molten sea of ten cubits from brim to brim, round in shape. Its height was five cubits; and a line of thirty\ncubits encircled it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 7:24"},"Under its brim around there were buds which encircled it for ten cubits, encircling the sea. The buds were in two rows,\ncast when it was cast. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 7:25"},"It stood on twelve oxen, three looking towards the north, and three looking towards the west, and three looking towards\nthe south, and three looking towards the east; and the sea was set on them above, and all their hindquarters were inward.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 7:26"},"It was a hand width thick. Its brim was worked like the brim of a cup, like the flower of a lily. It held two thousand\nbaths. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 7:27"},"He made the ten bases of bronze. The length of one base was four cubits, four cubits its width, and three cubits its\nheight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 7:28"},"The work of the bases was like this: they had panels; and there were panels between the ledges;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 7:29"},"and on the panels that were between the ledges were lions, oxen, and cherubim; and on the ledges there was a pedestal\nabove; and beneath the lions and oxen were wreaths of hanging work.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 7:30"},"Every base had four bronze wheels, and axles of bronze; and the four feet of it had supports. The supports were cast\nbeneath the basin, with wreaths at the side of each. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 7:31"},"Its mouth within the capital and above was a cubit. Its mouth was round after the work of a pedestal, a cubit and a half;\nand also on its mouth were engravings, and their panels were square, not round.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 7:32"},"The four wheels were underneath the panels; and the axles of the wheels were in the base. The height of a wheel was a\ncubit and half a cubit. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 7:33"},"The work of the wheels was like the work of a chariot wheel. Their axles, and their rims, and their spokes, and their\nnaves, were all of cast metal. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 7:34"},"There were four supports at the four corners of each base. Its supports were of the base itself.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 7:35"},"In the top of the base there was a round band half a cubit high; and on the top of the base its supports and its panels\nwere the same. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 7:36"},"On the plates of its supports, and on its panels, he engraved cherubim, lions, and palm trees, each in its space, with\nwreaths all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 7:37"},"He made the ten bases in this way: all of them had one casting, one measure, and one form.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 7:38"},"He made ten basins of bronze. One basin contained forty baths;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 bath is one tenth of a cor, or about 5.6 U. S. gallons or 21 litres, so 4 baths was about 224 gallons or 840\nlitres."]}],"caller":"+"}," and every basin was four cubits; and on every one of the ten bases one basin.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 7:39"},"He set the bases, five on the right side of the house, and five on the left side of the house. He set the sea on the\nright side of the house eastward and towards the south. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 7:40"},"Hiram made the pots, the shovels, and the basins. So Hiram finished doing all the work that he worked for king Sulaiman\nin the LORD’s house: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 7:41"},"the two pillars; the two bowls of the capitals that were on the top of the pillars; the two networks to cover the two\nbowls of the capitals that were on the top of the pillars; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 7:42"},"the four hundred pomegranates for the two networks; two rows of pomegranates for each network, to cover the two bowls of\nthe capitals that were on the pillars; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 7:43"},"the ten bases; the ten basins on the bases; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"1KI 7:44"},"the one sea; the twelve oxen under the sea; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"1KI 7:45"},"the pots; the shovels; and the basins: even all these vessels, which Hiram made for king Sulaiman, in the LORD’s house,\nwere of burnished bronze. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"1KI 7:46"},"The king cast them in the plain of the Jordan, in the clay ground between Succoth and Zarethan.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"1KI 7:47"},"Sulaiman left all the vessels unweighed, because there were so many of them. The weight of the bronze could not be\ndetermined. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"1KI 7:48"},"Sulaiman made all the vessels that were in the LORD’s house: the golden altar and the table that the show bread was on,\nof gold; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"1KI 7:49"},"and the lamp stands, five on the right side, and five on the left, before the inner sanctuary, of pure gold; and the\nflowers, the lamps, and the tongs, of gold; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"1KI 7:50"},"the cups, the snuffers, the basins, the spoons, and the fire pans, of pure gold; and the hinges, both for the doors of\nthe inner house, the most holy place, and for the doors of the house, of the temple, of gold.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"1KI 7:51"},"Thus all the work that king Sulaiman did in the LORD’s house was finished. Sulaiman brought in the things which Dawood\nhis father had dedicated, the silver, the gold, and the vessels, and put them in the treasuries of the LORD’s house.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"1KI 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 8:1"},"Then Sulaiman assembled the elders of Israel, with all the heads of the tribes, the princes of the fathers’ households of\nthe children of Israel, to king Sulaiman in Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the LORD’s covenant out of Dawood’s city, which\nis Zion. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 8:2"},"All the men of Israel assembled themselves to king Sulaiman at the feast, in the month Ethanim, which is the seventh\nmonth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 8:3"},"All the elders of Israel came, and the priests picked up the ark.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 8:4"},"They brought up the LORD’s ark, the Tent of Meeting, and all the holy vessels that were in the Tent. The priests and the\nLevites brought these up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 8:5"},"King Sulaiman and all the congregation of Israel, who were assembled to him, were with him before the ark, sacrificing\nsheep and cattle, that could not be counted or numbered for multitude.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 8:6"},"The priests brought in the ark of the LORD’s covenant to its place, into the inner sanctuary of the house, to the most\nholy place, even under the cherubim’s wings. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 8:7"},"For the cherubim spread their wings out over the place of the ark, and the cherubim covered the ark and its poles above.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 8:8"},"The poles were so long that the ends of the poles were seen from the holy place before the inner sanctuary; but they were\nnot seen outside. They are there to this day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 8:9"},"There was nothing in the ark except the two stone tablets which Musa put there at Horeb, when the LORD made a covenant\nwith the children of Israel, when they came out of the land of Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 8:10"},"It came to pass, when the priests had come out of the holy place, that the cloud filled the LORD’s house,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 8:11"},"so that the priests could not stand to minister by reason of the cloud; for the LORD’s glory filled the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 8:12"},"Then Sulaiman said, “The LORD has said that he would dwell in the thick darkness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 8:13"},"I have surely built you a house of habitation, a place for you to dwell in forever.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 8:14"},"The king turned his face around, and blessed all the assembly of Israel; and all the assembly of Israel stood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 8:15"},"He said, “Blessed is the LORD, Allah of Israel, who spoke with his mouth to Dawood your father, and has with his hand\nfulfilled it, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 8:16"},"‘Since the day that I brought my people Israel out of Egypt, I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel to build a\nhouse, that my name might be there; but I chose Dawood to be over my people Israel.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 8:17"},"“Now it was in the heart of Dawood my father to build a house for the name of the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 8:18"},"But the LORD said to Dawood my father, ‘Whereas it was in your heart to build a house for my name, you did well that it\nwas in your heart. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 8:19"},"Nevertheless, you shall not build the house; but your son who shall come out of your body, he shall build the house for\nmy name.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 8:20"},"The LORD has established his word that he spoke; for I have risen up in the place of Dawood my father, and I sit on the\nthrone of Israel, as the LORD promised, and have built the house for the name of the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 8:21"},"There I have set a place for the ark, in which is the LORD’s covenant, which he made with our fathers, when he brought\nthem out of the land of Egypt.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 8:22"},"Sulaiman stood before the LORD’s altar in the presence of all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands towards\nheaven; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 8:23"},"and he said, “LORD, Allah of Israel, there is no Allah like you, in heaven above, or on earth beneath; who keeps covenant\nand loving kindness with your servants, who walk before you with all their heart;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 8:24"},"who has kept with your servant Dawood my father that which you promised him. Yes, you spoke with your mouth, and have\nfulfilled it with your hand, as it is today. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 8:25"},"Now therefore, may LORD, Allah of Israel, keep with your servant Dawood my father that which you have promised him,\nsaying, ‘There shall not fail from you a man in my sight to sit on the throne of Israel, if only your children take heed to\ntheir way, to walk before me as you have walked before me.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 8:26"},"“Now therefore, Allah of Israel, please let your word be verified, which you spoke to your servant Dawood my father.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 8:27"},"But will Allah in very deed dwell on the earth? Behold, heaven and the heaven of heavens can’t contain you; how much less\nthis house that I have built! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 8:28"},"Yet have respect for the prayer of your servant, and for his supplication, LORD my Allah, to listen to the cry and to the\nprayer which your servant prays before you today; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 8:29"},"that your eyes may be open towards this house night and day, even towards the place of which you have said, ‘My name\nshall be there;’ to listen to the prayer which your servant prays towards this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 8:30"},"Listen to the supplication of your servant, and of your people Israel, when they pray towards this place. Yes, hear in\nheaven, your dwelling place; and when you hear, forgive. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 8:31"},"“If a man sins against his neighbour, and an oath is laid on him to cause him to swear, and he comes and swears before\nyour altar in this house; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 8:32"},"then hear in heaven, and act, and judge your servants, condemning the wicked, to bring his way on his own head, and\njustifying the righteous, to give him according to his righteousness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 8:33"},"“When your people Israel are struck down before the enemy, because they have sinned against you; if they turn again to\nyou, and confess your name, and pray and make supplication to you in this house;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 8:34"},"then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of your people Israel, and bring them again to the land which you gave to their\nfathers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 8:35"},"“When the sky is shut up, and there is no rain, because they have sinned against you; if they pray towards this place,\nand confess your name, and turn from their sin, when you afflict them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 8:36"},"then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of your servants, and of your people Israel, when you teach them the good way in\nwhich they should walk; and send rain on your land, which you have given to your people for an inheritance.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 8:37"},"“If there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence, if there is blight, mildew, locust or caterpillar; if their\nenemy besieges them in the land of their cities; whatever plague, whatever sickness there is;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 8:38"},"whatever prayer and supplication is made by any man, or by all your people Israel, who shall each know the plague of his\nown heart, and spread out his hands towards this house, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 8:39"},"then hear in heaven, your dwelling place, and forgive, and act, and give to every man according to all his ways, whose\nheart you know (for you, even you only, know the hearts of all the children of men);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 8:40"},"that they may fear you all the days that they live in the land which you gave to our fathers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 8:41"},"“Moreover concerning the foreigner, who is not of your people Israel, when he comes out of a far country for your name’s\nsake \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 8:42"},"(for they shall hear of your great name, and of your mighty hand, and of your outstretched arm); when he comes and prays\ntowards this house; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 8:43"},"hear in heaven, your dwelling place, and do according to all that the foreigner calls to you for; that all the peoples of\nthe earth may know your name, to fear you, as do your people Israel, and that they may know that this house which I have built\nis called by your name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"1KI 8:44"},"“If your people go out to battle against their enemy, by whatever way you shall send them, and they pray to the LORD\ntowards the city which you have chosen, and towards the house which I have built for your name;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"1KI 8:45"},"then hear in heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"1KI 8:46"},"If they sin against you (for there is no man who doesn’t sin), and you are angry with them, and deliver them to the\nenemy, so that they carry them away captive to the land of the enemy, far off or near;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"1KI 8:47"},"yet if they repent in the land where they are carried captive, and turn again, and make supplication to you in the land\nof those who carried them captive, saying, ‘We have sinned, and have done perversely; we have dealt wickedly;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"1KI 8:48"},"if they return to you with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their enemies, who carried them\ncaptive, and pray to you towards their land, which you gave to their fathers, the city which you have chosen, and the house\nwhich I have built for your name; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"1KI 8:49"},"then hear their prayer and their supplication in heaven, your dwelling place, and maintain their cause;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"1KI 8:50"},"and forgive your people who have sinned against you, and all their transgressions in which they have transgressed against\nyou; and give them compassion before those who carried them captive, that they may have compassion on them\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"1KI 8:51"},"(for they are your people, and your inheritance, which you brought out of Egypt, from the middle of the iron furnace);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"1KI 8:52"},"that your eyes may be open to the supplication of your servant, and to the supplication of your people Israel, to listen\nto them whenever they cry to you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"1KI 8:53"},"For you separated them from amongst all the peoples of the earth, to be your inheritance, as you spoke by Musa your\nservant, when you brought our fathers out of Egypt, Lord ALLAH.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"1KI 8:54"},"It was so, that when Sulaiman had finished praying all this prayer and supplication to the LORD, he arose from before the\nLORD’s altar, from kneeling on his knees with his hands spread out towards heaven.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"1KI 8:55"},"He stood, and blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"1KI 8:56"},"“Blessed be the LORD, who has given rest to his people Israel, according to all that he promised. There has not failed\none word of all his good promise, which he promised by Musa his servant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"1KI 8:57"},"May the LORD our Allah be with us, as he was with our fathers. Let him not leave us or forsake us;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"1KI 8:58"},"that he may incline our hearts to him, to walk in all his ways, and to keep his commandments, and his statutes, and his\nordinances, which he commanded our fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"1KI 8:59"},"Let these my words, with which I have made supplication before the LORD, be near to the LORD our Allah day and night,\nthat he may maintain the cause of his servant, and the cause of his people Israel, as every day requires;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"1KI 8:60"},"that all the peoples of the earth may know that the LORD himself is Allah. There is no one else.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"1KI 8:61"},"“Let your heart therefore be perfect with the LORD our Allah, to walk in his statutes, and to keep his commandments, as\nit is today.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"1KI 8:62"},"The king, and all Israel with him, offered sacrifice before the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63","sid":"1KI 8:63"},"Sulaiman offered for the sacrifice of peace offerings, which he offered to the LORD, twenty two thousand head of cattle,\nand one hundred and twenty thousand sheep. So the king and all the children of Israel dedicated the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64","sid":"1KI 8:64"},"The same day the king made the middle of the court holy that was before the LORD’s house; for there he offered the burnt\noffering, and the meal offering, and the fat of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar that was before the LORD was too\nlittle to receive the burnt offering, the meal offering, and the fat of the peace offerings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65","sid":"1KI 8:65"},"So Sulaiman held the feast at that time, and all Israel with him, a great assembly, from the entrance of Hamath to the\nbrook of Egypt, before the LORD our Allah, seven days and seven more days, even fourteen days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66","sid":"1KI 8:66"},"On the eighth day he sent the people away; and they blessed the king, and went to their tents joyful and glad in their\nhearts for all the goodness that the LORD had shown to Dawood his servant, and to Israel his people.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"1KI 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 9:1"},"When Sulaiman had finished the building of the LORD’s house, the king’s house, and all Sulaiman’s desire which he was\npleased to do, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 9:2"},"The LORD appeared to Sulaiman the second time, as he had appeared to him at Gibeon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 9:3"},"The LORD said to him, “I have heard your prayer and your supplication, that you have made before me. I have made this\nhouse holy, which you have built, to put my name there forever; and my eyes and my heart shall be there perpetually.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 9:4"},"As for you, if you will walk before me, as Dawood your father walked, in integrity of heart, and in uprightness, to do\naccording to all that I have commanded you, and will keep my statutes and my ordinances;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 9:5"},"then I will establish the throne of your kingdom over Israel forever, as I promised to Dawood your father, saying, ‘There\nshall not fail from you a man on the throne of Israel.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 9:6"},"But if you turn away from following me, you or your children, and not keep my commandments and my statutes which I have\nset before you, but go and serve other gods, and worship them; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 9:7"},"then I will cut off Israel out of the land which I have given them; and I will cast this house, which I have made holy for\nmy name, out of my sight; and Israel will be a proverb and a byword amongst all peoples.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 9:8"},"Though this house is so high, yet everyone who passes by it will be astonished and hiss; and they will say, ‘Why has the\nLORD done this to this land, and to this house?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 9:9"},"and they will answer, ‘Because they abandoned the LORD their Allah, who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt,\nand embraced other gods, and worshipped them, and served them. Therefore the LORD has brought all this evil on them.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 9:10"},"At the end of twenty years, in which Sulaiman had built the two houses, the LORD’s house and the king’s house\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 9:11"},"(now Hiram the king of Tyre had furnished Sulaiman with cedar trees and cypress trees, and with gold, according to all\nhis desire), King Sulaiman gave Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 9:12"},"Hiram came out of Tyre to see the cities which Sulaiman had given him; and they didn’t please him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 9:13"},"He said, “What cities are these which you have given me, my brother?” He called them the land of\nCabul",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Cabul” sounds like Hebrew for “good-for-nothing”."]}],"caller":"+"}," to this day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 9:14"},"Hiram sent to the king one hundred and twenty talents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 120 talents is about 3.6 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 9:15"},"This is the reason of the levy which king Sulaiman raised, to build the LORD’s house, his own house, Millo, Jerusalem’s\nwall, Hazor, Megiddo, and Gezer. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 9:16"},"Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up, taken Gezer, burnt it with fire, killed the Canaanites who lived in the city, and\ngiven it for a wedding gift to his daughter, Sulaiman’s wife. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 9:17"},"Sulaiman built in the land Gezer, Beth Horon the lower, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 9:18"},"Baalath, Tamar in the wilderness, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 9:19"},"all the storage cities that Sulaiman had, the cities for his chariots, the cities for his horsemen, and that which\nSulaiman desired to build for his pleasure in Jerusalem, and in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 9:20"},"As for all the people who were left of the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who\nwere not of the children of Israel; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 9:21"},"their children who were left after them in the land, whom the children of Israel were not able utterly to destroy, of\nthem Sulaiman raised a levy of bondservants to this day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 9:22"},"But of the children of Israel Sulaiman made no bondservants; but they were the men of war, his servants, his princes, his\ncaptains, and rulers of his chariots and of his horsemen. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 9:23"},"These were the five hundred and fifty chief officers who were over Sulaiman’s work, who ruled over the people who\nlaboured in the work. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 9:24"},"But Pharaoh’s daughter came up out of Dawood’s city to her house which Sulaiman had built for her. Then he built Millo.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 9:25"},"Sulaiman offered burnt offerings and peace offerings on the altar which he built to the LORD three times per year,\nburning incense with them, on the altar that was before the LORD. So he finished the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 9:26"},"King Sulaiman made a fleet of ships in Ezion Geber, which is beside Eloth, on the shore of the Red Sea, in the land of\nEdom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 9:27"},"Hiram sent in the fleet his servants, sailors who had knowledge of the sea, with the servants of Sulaiman.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 9:28"},"They came to Ophir, and fetched from there gold, four hundred and twenty\ntalents,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 420 talents is about 12.6 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," and brought it to king Sulaiman. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"1KI 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 10:1"},"When the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Sulaiman concerning the LORD’s name, she came to test him with hard\nquestions. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 10:2"},"She came to Jerusalem with a very great caravan, with camels that bore spices, very much gold, and precious stones; and\nwhen she had come to Sulaiman, she talked with him about all that was in her heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 10:3"},"Sulaiman answered all her questions. There wasn’t anything hidden from the king which he didn’t tell her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 10:4"},"When the queen of Sheba had seen all the wisdom of Sulaiman, the house that he had built,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 10:5"},"the food of his table, the sitting of his servants, the attendance of his officials, their clothing, his cup bearers, and\nhis ascent by which he went up to the LORD’s house; there was no more spirit in her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 10:6"},"She said to the king, “It was a true report that I heard in my own land of your acts, and of your wisdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 10:7"},"However I didn’t believe the words until I came and my eyes had seen it. Behold, not even half was told me! Your wisdom\nand prosperity exceed the fame which I heard. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 10:8"},"Happy are your men, happy are these your servants, who stand continually before you, who hear your wisdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 10:9"},"Blessed is Allah your LORD, who delighted in you, to set you on the throne of Israel. Because the LORD loved Israel\nforever, therefore he made you king, to do justice and righteousness.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 10:10"},"She gave the king one hundred and twenty talents of gold, and a very great quantity of spices, and precious stones. Never\nagain was there such an abundance of spices as these which the queen of Sheba gave to king Sulaiman.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 10:11"},"The fleet of Hiram that brought gold from Ophir, also brought in from Ophir great quantities of almug\ntrees",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["possibly an Indian sandalwood, with nice grain and a pleasant scent, and good for\nwoodworking"]}],"caller":"+"}," and precious stones. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 10:12"},"The king made of the almug trees pillars for the LORD’s house, and for the king’s house, harps also and stringed\ninstruments for the singers; no such almug trees came or were seen, to this day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 10:13"},"King Sulaiman gave to the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatever she asked, in addition to that which Sulaiman gave her\nof his royal bounty. So she turned and went to her own land, she and her servants.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 10:14"},"Now the weight of gold that came to Sulaiman in one year was six hundred and sixty-six\ntalents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 666 talents is about 20 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 10:15"},"in addition to that which the traders brought, and the traffic of the merchants, and of all the kings of the mixed\npeople, and of the governors of the country. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 10:16"},"King Sulaiman made two hundred bucklers of beaten gold; six hundred\nshekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.32 Troy ounces, so 600 shekels is about 6 kilograms or 13.2\npounds or 192 Troy ounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold went to one buckler. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 10:17"},"he made three hundred shields of beaten gold; three minas",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A mina is about 600 grams or 1.3 U. S. pounds."]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold went to one shield; and the king put them in the House\nof the Forest of Lebanon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 10:18"},"Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with the finest gold.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 10:19"},"There were six steps to the throne, and the top of the throne was round behind; and there were armrests on either side by\nthe place of the seat, and two lions standing beside the armrests.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 10:20"},"Twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other on the six steps. Nothing like it was made in any kingdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 10:21"},"All king Sulaiman’s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure\ngold. None were of silver, because it was considered of little value in the days of Sulaiman.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 10:22"},"For the king had a fleet of Tarshish at sea with Hiram’s fleet. Once every three years the fleet of Tarshish came,\nbringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and peacocks. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 10:23"},"So king Sulaiman exceeded all the kings of the earth in riches and in wisdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 10:24"},"All the earth sought the presence of Sulaiman, to hear his wisdom, which Allah had put in his heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 10:25"},"Year after year, every man brought his tribute, vessels of silver, vessels of gold, clothing, armour, spices, horses, and\nmules. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 10:26"},"Sulaiman gathered together chariots and horsemen. He had one thousand and four hundred chariots, and twelve thousand\nhorsemen, that he kept in the chariot cities and with the king at Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 10:27"},"The king made silver as common as stones in Jerusalem, and cedars as common as the sycamore trees that are in the\nlowland. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 10:28"},"The horses which Sulaiman had were brought out of Egypt. The king’s merchants received them in droves, each drove at a\nprice. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 10:29"},"A chariot came up and went out of Egypt for six hundred shekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver, and a horse for one hundred and fifty shekels; and\nso they exported them to all the kings of the Hittites, and to the kings of Syria.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"1KI 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 11:1"},"Now king Sulaiman loved many foreign women, together with the daughter of Pharaoh, women of the Moabites, Ammonites,\nEdomites, Sidonians, and Hittites; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 11:2"},"of the nations concerning which the LORD said to the children of Israel, “You shall not go amongst them, neither shall\nthey come amongst you; for surely they will turn away your heart after their gods.” Sulaiman joined to these in love.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 11:3"},"He had seven hundred wives, princesses, and three hundred concubines. His wives turned his heart away.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 11:4"},"When Sulaiman was old, his wives turned away his heart after other gods; and his heart was not perfect with the LORD his\nAllah, as the heart of Dawood his father was. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 11:5"},"For Sulaiman went after Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, and after Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 11:6"},"Sulaiman did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, and didn’t go fully after the LORD, as Dawood his father did.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 11:7"},"Then Sulaiman built a high place for Chemosh the abomination of Moab, on the mountain that is before Jerusalem, and for\nMolech the abomination of the children of Ammon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 11:8"},"So he did for all his foreign wives, who burnt incense and sacrificed to their gods.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 11:9"},"The LORD was angry with Sulaiman, because his heart was turned away from the LORD, Allah of Israel, who had appeared to\nhim twice, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 11:10"},"and had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go after other gods; but he didn’t keep that which the\nLORD commanded. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 11:11"},"Therefore the LORD said to Sulaiman, “Because this is done by you, and you have not kept my covenant and my statutes,\nwhich I have commanded you, I will surely tear the kingdom from you, and will give it to your servant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 11:12"},"Nevertheless, I will not do it in your days, for Dawood your father’s sake; but I will tear it out of your son’s hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 11:13"},"However I will not tear away all the kingdom; but I will give one tribe to your son, for Dawood my servant’s sake, and\nfor Jerusalem’s sake which I have chosen.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 11:14"},"The LORD raised up an adversary to Sulaiman: Hadad the Edomite. He was one of the king’s offspring in Edom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 11:15"},"For when Dawood was in Edom, and Joab the captain of the army had gone up to bury the slain, and had struck every male in\nEdom \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 11:16"},"(for Joab and all Israel remained there six months, until he had cut off every male in Edom);\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 11:17"},"Hadad fled, he and certain Edomites of his father’s servants with him, to go into Egypt, when Hadad was still a little\nchild. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 11:18"},"They arose out of Midian, and came to Paran; and they took men with them out of Paran, and they came to Egypt, to Pharaoh\nking of Egypt, who gave him a house, and appointed him food, and gave him land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 11:19"},"Hadad found great favour in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he gave him as wife the sister of his own wife, the sister of\nTahpenes the queen. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 11:20"},"The sister of Tahpenes bore him Genubath his son, whom Tahpenes weaned in Pharaoh’s house; and Genubath was in Pharaoh’s\nhouse amongst the sons of Pharaoh. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 11:21"},"When Hadad heard in Egypt that Dawood slept with his fathers, and that Joab the captain of the army was dead, Hadad said\nto Pharaoh, “Let me depart, that I may go to my own country.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 11:22"},"Then Pharaoh said to him, “But what have you lacked with me, that behold, you seek to go to your own country?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered, “Nothing, however only let me depart.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 11:23"},"Allah raised up an adversary to him, Rezon the son of Eliada, who had fled from his lord Hadadezer king of Zobah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 11:24"},"He gathered men to himself, and became captain over a troop, when Dawood killed them of Zobah. They went to Damascus, and\nlived there, and reigned in Damascus. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 11:25"},"He was an adversary to Israel all the days of Sulaiman, in addition to the mischief of Hadad. He abhorred Israel, and\nreigned over Syria. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 11:26"},"Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephraimite of Zeredah, a servant of Sulaiman, whose mother’s name was Zeruah, a widow, also\nlifted up his hand against the king. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 11:27"},"This was the reason why he lifted up his hand against the king: Sulaiman built Millo, and repaired the breach of his\nfather Dawood’s city. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 11:28"},"The man Jeroboam was a mighty man of valour; and Sulaiman saw the young man that he was industrious, and he put him in\ncharge of all the labour of the house of Yusuf. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 11:29"},"At that time, when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem, the prophet Ahijah the Shilonite found him on the way. Now Ahijah had\nclad himself with a new garment; and the two of them were alone in the field.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 11:30"},"Ahijah took the new garment that was on him, and tore it in twelve pieces.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 11:31"},"He said to Jeroboam, “Take ten pieces; for the LORD, Allah of Israel, says, ‘Behold, I will tear the kingdom out of the\nhand of Sulaiman, and will give ten tribes to you \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 11:32"},"(but he shall have one tribe, for my servant Dawood’s sake and for Jerusalem’s sake, the city which I have chosen out of\nall the tribes of Israel); \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 11:33"},"because that they have forsaken me, and have worshipped Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of Moab,\nand Milcom the god of the children of Ammon. They have not walked in my ways, to do that which is right in my eyes, and to keep\nmy statutes and my ordinances, as Dawood his father did. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 11:34"},"“‘However I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand; but I will make him prince all the days of his life, for\nDawood my servant’s sake whom I chose, who kept my commandments and my statutes;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 11:35"},"but I will take the kingdom out of his son’s hand, and will give it to you, even ten tribes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 11:36"},"I will give one tribe to his son, that Dawood my servant may have a lamp always before me in Jerusalem, the city which I\nhave chosen for myself to put my name there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 11:37"},"I will take you, and you shall reign according to all that your soul desires, and shall be king over Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 11:38"},"It shall be, if you will listen to all that I command you, and will walk in my ways, and do that which is right in my\neyes, to keep my statutes and my commandments, as Dawood my servant did; that I will be with you, and will build you a sure\nhouse, as I built for Dawood, and will give Israel to you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 11:39"},"I will afflict the offspring of Dawood for this, but not forever.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 11:40"},"Therefore Sulaiman sought to kill Jeroboam; but Jeroboam arose, and fled into Egypt, to Shishak king of Egypt, and was in\nEgypt until the death of Sulaiman. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 11:41"},"Now the rest of the acts of Sulaiman, and all that he did, and his wisdom, aren’t they written in the book of the acts of\nSulaiman? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 11:42"},"The time that Sulaiman reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 11:43"},"Sulaiman slept with his fathers, and was buried in his father Dawood’s city; and Rehoboam his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"1KI 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 12:1"},"Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem to make him king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 12:2"},"When Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it (for he was yet in Egypt, where he had fled from the presence of king Sulaiman,\nand Jeroboam lived in Egypt, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 12:3"},"and they sent and called him), Jeroboam and all the assembly of Israel came, and spoke to Rehoboam, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 12:4"},"“Your father made our yoke difficult. Now therefore make the hard service of your father, and his heavy yoke which he put\non us, lighter, and we will serve you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 12:5"},"He said to them, “Depart for three days, then come back to me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So the people departed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 12:6"},"King Rehoboam took counsel with the old men, who had stood before Sulaiman his father while he yet lived, saying, “What\ncounsel do you give me to answer these people?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 12:7"},"They replied, “If you will be a servant to this people today, and will serve them, and answer them with good words, then\nthey will be your servants forever.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 12:8"},"But he abandoned the counsel of the old men which they had given him, and took counsel with the young men who had grown up\nwith him, who stood before him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 12:9"},"He said to them, “What counsel do you give, that we may answer these people, who have spoken to me, saying, ‘Make the yoke\nthat your father put on us lighter?’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 12:10"},"The young men who had grown up with him said to him, “Tell these people who spoke to you, saying, ‘Your father made our\nyoke heavy, but make it lighter to us;’ tell them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father’s waist.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 12:11"},"Now my father burdened you with a heavy yoke, but I will add to your yoke. My father chastised you with whips, but I will\nchastise you with scorpions.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 12:12"},"So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king asked, saying, “Come to me again the third\nday.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 12:13"},"The king answered the people roughly, and abandoned the counsel of the old men which they had given him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 12:14"},"and spoke to them according to the counsel of the young men, saying, “My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to\nyour yoke. My father chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scorpions.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 12:15"},"So the king didn’t listen to the people; for it was a thing brought about from the LORD, that he might establish his\nword, which the LORD spoke by Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 12:16"},"When all Israel saw that the king didn’t listen to them, the people answered the king, saying, “What portion have we in\nDawood? We don’t have an inheritance in the son of Jesse. To your tents, Israel! Now see to your own house, Dawood.” So Israel\ndeparted to their tents. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 12:17"},"But as for the children of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 12:18"},"Then king Rehoboam sent Adoram, who was over the men subject to forced labour; and all Israel stoned him to death with\nstones. King Rehoboam hurried to get himself up to his chariot, to flee to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 12:19"},"So Israel rebelled against Dawood’s house to this day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 12:20"},"When all Israel heard that Jeroboam had returned, they sent and called him to the congregation, and made him king over\nall Israel. There was no one who followed Dawood’s house, except for the tribe of Judah only.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 12:21"},"When Rehoboam had come to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house of Judah and the tribe of Benjamin, a hundred and eighty\nthousand chosen men, who were warriors, to fight against the house of Israel, to bring the kingdom again to Rehoboam the son of\nSulaiman. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 12:22"},"But the word of Allah came to Shemaiah the man of Allah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 12:23"},"“Speak to Rehoboam the son of Sulaiman, king of Judah, and to all the house of Judah and Benjamin, and to the rest of the\npeople, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 12:24"},"‘The LORD says, “You shall not go up or fight against your brothers, the children of Israel. Everyone return to his\nhouse; for this thing is from me.”’” So they listened to the LORD’s word, and returned and went their way, according to the\nLORD’s word. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 12:25"},"Then Jeroboam built Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and lived in it; and he went out from there, and built\nPenuel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 12:26"},"Jeroboam said in his heart, “Now the kingdom will return to Dawood’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 12:27"},"If this people goes up to offer sacrifices in the LORD’s house at Jerusalem, then the heart of this people will turn\nagain to their lord, even to Rehoboam king of Judah; and they will kill me, and return to Rehoboam king of Judah.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 12:28"},"So the king took counsel, and made two calves of gold; and he said to them, “It is too much for you to go up to\nJerusalem. Look and behold your gods, Israel, which brought you up out of the land of Egypt!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 12:29"},"He set the one in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 12:30"},"This thing became a sin; for the people went even as far as Dan to worship before the one there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 12:31"},"He made houses of high places, and made priests from amongst all the people, who were not of the sons of Levi.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 12:32"},"Jeroboam ordained a feast in the eighth month, on the fifteenth day of the month, like the feast that is in Judah, and he\nwent up to the altar. He did so in Bethel, sacrificing to the calves that he had made, and he placed in Bethel the priests of\nthe high places that he had made. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 12:33"},"He went up to the altar which he had made in Bethel on the fifteenth day in the eighth month, even in the month which he\nhad devised of his own heart; and he ordained a feast for the children of Israel, and went up to the altar, to burn incense.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"1KI 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 13:1"},"Behold, a man of Allah came out of Judah by the LORD’s word to Bethel; and Jeroboam was standing by the altar to burn\nincense. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 13:2"},"He cried against the altar by the LORD’s word, and said, “Altar! Altar! the LORD says: ‘Behold, a son will be born to\nDawood’s house, Josiah by name. On you he will sacrifice the priests of the high places who burn incense on you, and they will\nburn men’s bones on you.’” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 13:3"},"He gave a sign the same day, saying, “This is the sign which the LORD has spoken: Behold, the altar will be split apart,\nand the ashes that are on it will be poured out.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 13:4"},"When the king heard the saying of the man of Allah, which he cried against the altar in Bethel, Jeroboam put out his hand\nfrom the altar, saying, “Seize him!” His hand, which he put out against him, dried up, so that he could not draw it back again\nto himself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 13:5"},"The altar was also split apart, and the ashes poured out from the altar, according to the sign which the man of Allah had\ngiven by the LORD’s word. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 13:6"},"The king answered the man of Allah, “Now intercede for the favour of Allah your LORD, and pray for me, that my hand may be\nrestored me again.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The man of Allah interceded with the LORD, and the king’s hand was restored to him again, and became as it was before.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 13:7"},"The king said to the man of Allah, “Come home with me, and refresh yourself, and I will give you a reward.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 13:8"},"The man of Allah said to the king, “Even if you gave me half of your house, I would not go in with you, neither would I\neat bread nor drink water in this place; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 13:9"},"for so was it commanded me by the LORD’s word, saying, ‘You shall eat no bread, drink no water, and don’t return by the\nway that you came.’” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 13:10"},"So he went another way, and didn’t return by the way that he came to Bethel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 13:11"},"Now an old prophet lived in Bethel, and one of his sons came and told him all the works that the man of Allah had done\nthat day in Bethel. They also told their father the words which he had spoken to the king.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 13:12"},"Their father said to them, “Which way did he go?” Now his sons had seen which way the man of Allah went, who came from\nJudah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 13:13"},"He said to his sons, “Saddle the donkey for me.” So they saddled the donkey for him; and he rode on it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 13:14"},"He went after the man of Allah, and found him sitting under an oak. He said to him, “Are you the man of Allah who came\nfrom Judah?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “I am.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 13:15"},"Then he said to him, “Come home with me, and eat bread.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 13:16"},"He said, “I may not return with you, nor go in with you. I will not eat bread or drink water with you in this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 13:17"},"For it was said to me by the LORD’s word, ‘You shall eat no bread or drink water there, and don’t turn again to go by the\nway that you came.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 13:18"},"He said to him, “I also am a prophet as you are; and an angel spoke to me by the LORD’s word, saying, ‘Bring him back\nwith you into your house, that he may eat bread and drink water.’” He lied to him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 13:19"},"So he went back with him, ate bread in his house, and drank water.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 13:20"},"As they sat at the table, the LORD’s word came to the prophet who brought him back;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 13:21"},"and he cried out to the man of Allah who came from Judah, saying, “The LORD says, ‘Because you have been disobedient to\nthe LORD’s mouth, and have not kept the commandment which Allah your LORD commanded you,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 13:22"},"but came back, and have eaten bread and drank water in the place of which he said to you, “Eat no bread, and drink no\nwater;” your body will not come to the tomb of your fathers.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 13:23"},"After he had eaten bread, and after he drank, he saddled the donkey for the prophet whom he had brought back.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 13:24"},"When he had gone, a lion met him by the way and killed him. His body was thrown on the path, and the donkey stood by it.\nThe lion also stood by the body. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 13:25"},"Behold, men passed by, and saw the body thrown on the path, and the lion standing by the body; and they came and told it\nin the city where the old prophet lived. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 13:26"},"When the prophet who brought him back from the way heard of it, he said, “It is the man of Allah who was disobedient to\nthe LORD’s mouth. Therefore the LORD has delivered him to the lion, which has mauled him and slain him, according to the LORD’s\nword, which he spoke to him.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 13:27"},"He said to his sons, saying, “Saddle the donkey for me,” and they saddled it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 13:28"},"He went and found his body thrown on the path, and the donkey and the lion standing by the body. The lion had not eaten\nthe body, nor mauled the donkey. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 13:29"},"The prophet took up the body of the man of Allah, and laid it on the donkey, and brought it back. He came to the city of\nthe old prophet to mourn, and to bury him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 13:30"},"He laid his body in his own grave; and they mourned over him, saying, “Alas, my brother!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 13:31"},"After he had buried him, he spoke to his sons, saying, “When I am dead, bury me in the tomb in which the man of Allah is\nburied. Lay my bones beside his bones. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 13:32"},"For the saying which he cried by the LORD’s word against the altar in Bethel, and against all the houses of the high\nplaces which are in the cities of Samaria, will surely happen.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 13:33"},"After this thing Jeroboam didn’t return from his evil way, but again made priests of the high places from amongst all the\npeople. Whoever wanted to, he consecrated him, that there might be priests of the high places.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 13:34"},"This thing became sin to the house of Jeroboam, even to cut it off, and to destroy it from off the surface of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"1KI 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 14:1"},"At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam became sick. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 14:2"},"Jeroboam said to his wife, “Please get up and disguise yourself, so that you won’t be recognised as Jeroboam’s wife. Go to\nShiloh. Behold, Ahijah the prophet is there, who said that I would be king over this people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 14:3"},"Take with you ten loaves of bread, some cakes, and a jar of honey, and go to him. He will tell you what will become of the\nchild.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 14:4"},"Jeroboam’s wife did so, and arose, and went to Shiloh, and came to Ahijah’s house. Now Ahijah could not see; for his eyes\nwere set by reason of his age. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 14:5"},"The LORD said to Ahijah, “Behold, Jeroboam’s wife is coming to enquire of you concerning her son; for he is sick. Tell her\nsuch and such; for it will be, when she comes in, that she will pretend to be another woman.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 14:6"},"So when Ahijah heard the sound of her feet as she came in at the door, he said, “Come in, Jeroboam’s wife! Why do you\npretend to be another? For I am sent to you with heavy news. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 14:7"},"Go, tell Jeroboam, ‘The LORD, Allah of Israel, says: “Because I exalted you from amongst the people, and made you prince\nover my people Israel, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 14:8"},"and tore the kingdom away from Dawood’s house, and gave it you; and yet you have not been as my servant Dawood, who kept\nmy commandments, and who followed me with all his heart, to do that only which was right in my eyes,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 14:9"},"but have done evil above all who were before you, and have gone and made for yourself other gods, molten images, to\nprovoke me to anger, and have cast me behind your back; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 14:10"},"therefore, behold, I will bring evil on the house of Jeroboam, and will cut off from Jeroboam everyone who urinates on a\nwall,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, male"]}],"caller":"+"}," he who is shut up and he who is left at large in Israel, and will utterly sweep away the\nhouse of Jeroboam, as a man sweeps away dung, until it is all gone.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 14:11"},"The dogs will eat he who belongs to Jeroboam who dies in the city; and the birds of the sky will eat he who dies in the\nfield: for the LORD has spoken it.”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 14:12"},"Arise therefore, and go to your house. When your feet enter into the city, the child will die.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 14:13"},"All Israel will mourn for him and bury him; for he only of Jeroboam will come to the grave, because in him there is found\nsome good thing towards the LORD, Allah of Israel, in the house of Jeroboam.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 14:14"},"Moreover the LORD will raise up a king for himself over Israel, who will cut off the house of Jeroboam. This is the day!\nWhat? Even now. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 14:15"},"For the LORD will strike Israel, as a reed is shaken in the water; and he will root up Israel out of this good land which\nhe gave to their fathers, and will scatter them beyond the River,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Euphrates."]}],"caller":"+"}," because they have made their Asherah poles, provoking the LORD to anger.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 14:16"},"He will give Israel up because of the sins of Jeroboam, which he has sinned, and with which he has made Israel to sin.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 14:17"},"Jeroboam’s wife arose and departed, and came to Tirzah. As she came to the threshold of the house, the child died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 14:18"},"All Israel buried him and mourned for him, according to the LORD’s word, which he spoke by his servant Ahijah the\nprophet. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 14:19"},"The rest of the acts of Jeroboam, how he fought, and how he reigned, behold, they are written in the book of the\nchronicles of the kings of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 14:20"},"The days which Jeroboam reigned were twenty two years, then he slept with his fathers, and Nadab his son reigned in his\nplace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 14:21"},"Rehoboam the son of Sulaiman reigned in Judah. Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned\nseventeen years in Jerusalem, the city which the LORD had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, to put his name there. His\nmother’s name was Naamah the Ammonitess. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 14:22"},"Judah did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, and they provoked him to jealousy with their sins which they\ncommitted, above all that their fathers had done. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 14:23"},"For they also built for themselves high places, sacred pillars, and Asherah poles on every high hill and under every\ngreen tree. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 14:24"},"There were also sodomites in the land. They did according to all the abominations of the nations which the LORD drove out\nbefore the children of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 14:25"},"In the fifth year of king Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 14:26"},"and he took away the treasures of the LORD’s house, and the treasures of the king’s house. He even took away all of it,\nincluding all the gold shields which Sulaiman had made. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 14:27"},"King Rehoboam made shields of bronze in their place, and committed them to the hands of the captains of the guard, who\nkept the door of the king’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 14:28"},"It was so, that as often as the king went into the LORD’s house, the guard bore them, and brought them back into the\nguard room. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 14:29"},"Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam, and all that he did, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings\nof Judah? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 14:30"},"There was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 14:31"},"Rehoboam slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in Dawood’s city. His mother’s name was Naamah the\nAmmonitess. Abijam his son reigned in his place. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"1KI 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 15:1"},"Now in the eighteenth year of king Jeroboam the son of Nebat, Abijam began to reign over Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 15:2"},"He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 15:3"},"He walked in all the sins of his father, which he had done before him; and his heart was not perfect with the LORD his\nAllah, as the heart of Dawood his father. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 15:4"},"Nevertheless for Dawood’s sake, the LORD his Allah gave him a lamp in Jerusalem, to set up his son after him, and to\nestablish Jerusalem; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 15:5"},"because Dawood did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, and didn’t turn away from anything that he commanded him all\nthe days of his life, except only in the matter of Uriah the Hittite.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 15:6"},"Now there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 15:7"},"The rest of the acts of Abijam, and all that he did, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of\nJudah? There was war between Abijam and Jeroboam. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 15:8"},"Abijam slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Dawood’s city; and Asa his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 15:9"},"In the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa began to reign over Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 15:10"},"He reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 15:11"},"Asa did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, as Dawood his father did.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 15:12"},"He put away the sodomites out of the land, and removed all the idols that his fathers had made.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 15:13"},"He also removed Maacah his mother from being queen, because she had made an abominable image for an Asherah. Asa cut down\nher image and burnt it at the brook Kidron. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 15:14"},"But the high places were not taken away. Nevertheless the heart of Asa was perfect with the LORD all his days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 15:15"},"He brought into the LORD’s house the things that his father had dedicated, and the things that he himself had dedicated:\nsilver, gold, and utensils. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 15:16"},"There was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 15:17"},"Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah, and built Ramah, that he might not allow anyone to go out or come in to Asa\nking of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 15:18"},"Then Asa took all the silver and the gold that was left in the treasures of the LORD’s house, and the treasures of the\nking’s house, and delivered it into the hand of his servants. Then King Asa sent them to Ben Hadad, the son of Tabrimmon, the\nson of Hezion, king of Syria, who lived at Damascus, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 15:19"},"“There is a treaty between me and you, between my father and your father. Behold, I have sent to you a present of silver\nand gold. Go, break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, that he may depart from me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 15:20"},"Ben Hadad listened to king Asa, and sent the captains of his armies against the cities of Israel, and struck Ijon, and\nDan, and Habil Beth Maacah, and all Chinneroth, with all the land of Naphtali.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 15:21"},"When Baasha heard of it, he stopped building Ramah, and lived in Tirzah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 15:22"},"Then king Asa made a proclamation to all Judah. No one was exempted. They carried away the stones of Ramah, and its\ntimber, with which Baasha had built; and king Asa used it to build Geba of Benjamin, and Mizpah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 15:23"},"Now the rest of all the acts of Asa, and all his might, and all that he did, and the cities which he built, aren’t they\nwritten in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? But in the time of his old age he was diseased in his feet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 15:24"},"Asa slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in his father Dawood’s city; and Jehoshaphat his son reigned\nin his place. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 15:25"},"Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second year of Asa king of Judah; and he reigned over Israel\ntwo years. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 15:26"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin with which he made\nIsrael to sin. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 15:27"},"Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house of Issachar, conspired against him; and Baasha struck him at Gibbethon, which\nbelonged to the Philistines; for Nadab and all Israel were besieging Gibbethon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 15:28"},"Even in the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha killed him, and reigned in his place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 15:29"},"As soon as he was king, he struck all the house of Jeroboam. He didn’t leave to Jeroboam any who breathed, until he had\ndestroyed him; according to the saying of the LORD, which he spoke by his servant Ahijah the Shilonite;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 15:30"},"for the sins of Jeroboam which he sinned, and with which he made Israel to sin, because of his provocation with which he\nprovoked the LORD, Allah of Israel, to anger. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 15:31"},"Now the rest of the acts of Nadab, and all that he did, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of\nIsrael? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 15:32"},"There was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 15:33"},"In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah began to reign over all Israel in Tirzah for twenty-four\nyears. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 15:34"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, and walked in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin with which he made\nIsrael to sin. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"1KI 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 16:1"},"The LORD’s word came to Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 16:2"},"“Because I exalted you out of the dust, and made you prince over my people Israel, and you have walked in the way of\nJeroboam, and have made my people Israel to sin, to provoke me to anger with their sins;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 16:3"},"behold, I will utterly sweep away Baasha and his house; and I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of\nNebat. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 16:4"},"The dogs will eat Baasha’s descendants who die in the city; and he who dies of his in the field, the birds of the sky will\neat.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 16:5"},"Now the rest of the acts of Baasha, and what he did, and his might, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles of\nthe kings of Israel? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 16:6"},"Baasha slept with his fathers, and was buried in Tirzah; and Elah his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 16:7"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came by the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha and against his house, both because of\nall the evil that he did in the LORD’s sight, to provoke him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house of\nJeroboam, and because he struck him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 16:8"},"In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha began to reign over Israel in Tirzah for two years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 16:9"},"His servant Zimri, captain of half his chariots, conspired against him. Now he was in Tirzah, drinking himself drunk in\nthe house of Arza, who was over the household in Tirzah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 16:10"},"and Zimri went in and struck him, and killed him, in the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his\nplace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 16:11"},"When he began to reign, as soon as he sat on his throne, he attacked all the house of Baasha. He didn’t leave him a\nsingle one who urinates on a wall",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, male"]}],"caller":"+"}," amongst his relatives or his friends.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 16:12"},"Thus Zimri destroyed all the house of Baasha, according to the LORD’s word, which he spoke against Baasha by Jehu the\nprophet, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 16:13"},"for all the sins of Baasha, and the sins of Elah his son, which they sinned, and with which they made Israel to sin, to\nprovoke the LORD, Allah of Israel, to anger with their vanities.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 16:14"},"Now the rest of the acts of Elah, and all that he did, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of\nIsrael? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 16:15"},"In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned seven days in Tirzah. Now the people were encamped against\nGibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 16:16"},"The people who were encamped heard that Zimri had conspired, and had also killed the king. Therefore all Israel made\nOmri, the captain of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 16:17"},"Omri went up from Gibbethon, and all Israel with him, and they besieged Tirzah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 16:18"},"When Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the fortified part of the king’s house, and burnt the king’s house\nover him with fire, and died, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 16:19"},"for his sins which he sinned in doing that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, in walking in the way of Jeroboam, and in\nhis sin which he did, to make Israel to sin. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 16:20"},"Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and his treason that he committed, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles\nof the kings of Israel? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 16:21"},"Then the people of Israel were divided into two parts: half of the people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him\nking; and half followed Omri. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 16:22"},"But the people who followed Omri prevailed against the people who followed Tibni the son of Ginath; so Tibni died, and\nOmri reigned. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 16:23"},"In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri began to reign over Israel for twelve years. He reigned six years in\nTirzah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 16:24"},"He bought the hill Samaria of Shemer for two talents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:24\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds."]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver; and he built on the hill, and called the name of the city which\nhe built Samaria, after the name of Shemer, the owner of the hill.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 16:25"},"Omri did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, and dealt wickedly above all who were before him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 16:26"},"For he walked in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and in his sins with which he made Israel to sin, to provoke\nthe LORD, Allah of Israel, to anger with their vanities. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 16:27"},"Now the rest of the acts of Omri which he did, and his might that he showed, aren’t they written in the book of the\nchronicles of the kings of Israel? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 16:28"},"So Omri slept with his fathers, and was buried in Samaria; and Ahab his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 16:29"},"In the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, Ahab the son of Omri began to reign over Israel. Ahab the son of Omri\nreigned over Israel in Samaria twenty-two years. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 16:30"},"Ahab the son of Omri did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight above all that were before him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 16:31"},"As if it had been a light thing for him to walk in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, he took as wife Jezebel the\ndaughter of Ethbaal king of the Sidonians, and went and served Baal, and worshipped him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 16:32"},"He raised up an altar for Baal in the house of Baal, which he had built in Samaria.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 16:33"},"Ahab made the Asherah; and Ahab did more yet to provoke the LORD, Allah of Israel, to anger than all the kings of Israel\nwho were before him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 16:34"},"In his days Hiel the Bethelite built Jericho. He laid its foundation with the loss of Abiram his firstborn, and set up\nits gates with the loss of his youngest son Segub, according to the LORD’s word, which he spoke by Joshua the son of Nun.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"1KI 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 17:1"},"Ilyas the Tishbite, who was one of the settlers of Gilead, said to Ahab, “As the LORD, Allah of Israel, lives, before whom\nI stand, there shall not be dew nor rain these years, but according to my word.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 17:2"},"Then the LORD’s word came to him, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 17:3"},"“Go away from here, turn eastward, and hide yourself by the brook Cherith, that is before the Jordan.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 17:4"},"You shall drink from the brook. I have commanded the ravens to feed you there.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 17:5"},"So he went and did according to the LORD’s word; for he went and lived by the brook Cherith that is before the Jordan.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 17:6"},"The ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning, and bread and meat in the evening; and he drank from the brook.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 17:7"},"After a while, the brook dried up, because there was no rain in the land.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 17:8"},"The LORD’s word came to him, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 17:9"},"“Arise, go to Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and stay there. Behold, I have commanded a widow there to sustain you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 17:10"},"So he arose and went to Zarephath; and when he came to the gate of the city, behold, a widow was there gathering sticks.\nHe called to her, and said, “Please get me a little water in a jar, that I may drink.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 17:11"},"As she was going to get it, he called to her, and said, “Please bring me a morsel of bread in your hand.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 17:12"},"She said, “As Allah your LORD lives, I don’t have a cake, but a handful of meal in a jar, and a little oil in a jar.\nBehold, I am gathering two sticks, that I may go in and bake it for me and my son, that we may eat it, and die.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 17:13"},"Ilyas said to her, “Don’t be afraid. Go and do as you have said; but make me a little cake from it first, and bring it\nout to me, and afterward make some for you and for your son. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 17:14"},"For the LORD, Allah of Israel says, ‘The jar of meal will not run out, and the jar of oil will not fail, until the day\nthat the LORD sends rain on the earth.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 17:15"},"She went and did according to the saying of Ilyas; and she, and he, and her house, ate many days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 17:16"},"The jar of meal didn’t run out, and the jar of oil didn’t fail, according to the LORD’s word, which he spoke by Ilyas.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 17:17"},"After these things, the son of the woman, the mistress of the house, became sick; and his sickness was so severe that\nthere was no breath left in him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 17:18"},"She said to Ilyas, “What have I to do with you, you man of Allah? You have come to me to bring my sin to memory, and to\nkill my son!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 17:19"},"He said to her, “Give me your son.” He took him out of her bosom, and carried him up into the room where he stayed, and\nlaid him on his own bed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 17:20"},"He cried to the LORD, and said, “LORD my Allah, have you also brought evil on the widow with whom I am staying, by\nkilling her son?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 17:21"},"He stretched himself on the child three times, and cried to the LORD, and said, “LORD my Allah, please let this child’s\nsoul come into him again.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 17:22"},"The LORD listened to the voice of Ilyas; and the soul of the child came into him again, and he revived.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 17:23"},"Ilyas took the child, and brought him down out of the room into the house, and delivered him to his mother; and Ilyas\nsaid, “Behold, your son lives.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 17:24"},"The woman said to Ilyas, “Now I know that you are a man of Allah, and that the LORD’s word in your mouth is truth.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"1KI 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 18:1"},"After many days, the LORD’s word came to Ilyas, in the third year, saying, “Go, show yourself to Ahab; and I will send\nrain on the earth.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 18:2"},"Ilyas went to show himself to Ahab. The famine was severe in Samaria.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 18:3"},"Ahab called Obadiah, who was over the household. (Now Obadiah feared the LORD greatly;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 18:4"},"for when Jezebel cut off the LORD’s prophets, Obadiah took one hundred prophets, and hid them by fifty in a cave, and fed\nthem with bread and water.) \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 18:5"},"Ahab said to Obadiah, “Go through the land, to all the springs of water, and to all the brooks. Perhaps we may find grass\nand save the horses and mules alive, that we not lose all the animals.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 18:6"},"So they divided the land between them to pass throughout it. Ahab went one way by himself, and Obadiah went another way by\nhimself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 18:7"},"As Obadiah was on the way, behold, Ilyas met him. He recognised him, and fell on his face, and said, “Is it you, my lord\nIlyas?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 18:8"},"He answered him, “It is I. Go, tell your lord, ‘Behold, Ilyas is here!’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 18:9"},"He said, “How have I sinned, that you would deliver your servant into the hand of Ahab, to kill me?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 18:10"},"As Allah your LORD lives, there is no nation or kingdom where my lord has not sent to seek you. When they said, ‘He is\nnot here,’ he took an oath of the kingdom and nation, that they didn’t find you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 18:11"},"Now you say, ‘Go, tell your lord, “Behold, Ilyas is here.”’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 18:12"},"It will happen, as soon as I leave you, that the LORD’s Spirit will carry you I don’t know where; and so when I come and\ntell Ahab, and he can’t find you, he will kill me. But I, your servant, have feared the LORD from my youth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 18:13"},"Wasn’t it told my lord what I did when Jezebel killed the LORD’s prophets, how I hid one hundred men of the LORD’s\nprophets with fifty to a cave, and fed them with bread and water?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 18:14"},"Now you say, ‘Go, tell your lord, “Behold, Ilyas is here”.’ He will kill me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 18:15"},"Ilyas said, “As the LORD of Armies lives, before whom I stand, I will surely show myself to him today.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 18:16"},"So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and told him; and Ahab went to meet Ilyas.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 18:17"},"When Ahab saw Ilyas, Ahab said to him, “Is that you, you troubler of Israel?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 18:18"},"He answered, “I have not troubled Israel; but you, and your father’s house, in that you have forsaken the LORD’s\ncommandments, and you have followed the Baals. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 18:19"},"Now therefore send, and gather to me all Israel to Mount Carmel, and four hundred and fifty of the prophets of Baal, and\nfour hundred of the prophets of the Asherah, who eat at Jezebel’s table.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 18:20"},"So Ahab sent to all the children of Israel, and gathered the prophets together to Mount Carmel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 18:21"},"Ilyas came near to all the people, and said, “How long will you waver between the two sides? If the LORD is Allah, follow\nhim; but if Baal, then follow him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The people didn’t say a word. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 18:22"},"Then Ilyas said to the people, “I, even I only, am left as a prophet of the LORD; but Baal’s prophets are four hundred\nand fifty men. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 18:23"},"Let them therefore give us two bulls; and let them choose one bull for themselves, and cut it in pieces, and lay it on\nthe wood, and put no fire under; and I will dress the other bull, and lay it on the wood, and put no fire under it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 18:24"},"You call on the name of your god, and I will call on the LORD’s name. The Allah who answers by fire, let him be Allah.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["All the people answered, “What you say is good.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 18:25"},"Ilyas said to the prophets of Baal, “Choose one bull for yourselves, and dress it first; for you are many; and call on\nthe name of your god, but put no fire under it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 18:26"},"They took the bull which was given them, and they dressed it, and called on the name of Baal from morning even until\nnoon, saying, “Baal, hear us!” But there was no voice, and nobody answered. They leapt about the altar which was made.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 18:27"},"At noon, Ilyas mocked them, and said, “Cry aloud; for he is a god. Either he is deep in thought, or he has gone\nsomewhere, or he is on a journey, or perhaps he sleeps and must be awakened.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 18:28"},"They cried aloud, and cut themselves in their way with knives and lances, until the blood gushed out on them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 18:29"},"When midday was past, they prophesied until the time of the evening offering; but there was no voice, no answer, and\nnobody paid attention. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 18:30"},"Ilyas said to all the people, “Come near to me!”; and all the people came near to him. He repaired the LORD’s altar that\nhad been thrown down. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 18:31"},"Ilyas took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Yaqub, to whom the LORD’s word came,\nsaying, “Israel shall be your name.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 18:32"},"With the stones he built an altar in the LORD’s name. He made a trench around the altar, large enough to contain two\nseahs",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 seah is about 7 litres or 1.9 gallons or 0.8\npecks"]}],"caller":"+"}," of seed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 18:33"},"He put the wood in order, and cut the bull in pieces, and laid it on the wood. He said, “Fill four jars with water, and\npour it on the burnt offering, and on the wood.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 18:34"},"He said, “Do it a second time;” and they did it the second time. He said, “Do it a third time;” and they did it the third\ntime. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 18:35"},"The water ran around the altar; and he also filled the trench with water.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 18:36"},"At the time of the evening offering, Ilyas the prophet came near, and said, “LORD, Allah of Ibrahim, of Isḥāq, and of\nIsrael, let it be known today that you are Allah in Israel, and that I am your servant, and that I have done all these things\nat your word. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 18:37"},"Hear me, LORD, hear me, that this people may know that you, LORD, are Allah, and that you have turned their heart back\nagain.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 18:38"},"Then the LORD’s fire fell, and consumed the burnt offering, the wood, the stones, and the dust, and licked up the water\nthat was in the trench. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 18:39"},"When all the people saw it, they fell on their faces. They said, “The LORD, he is Allah! the LORD, he is Allah!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 18:40"},"Ilyas said to them, “Seize the prophets of Baal! Don’t let one of them escape!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They seized them; and Ilyas brought them down to the brook Kishon, and killed them there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 18:41"},"Ilyas said to Ahab, “Get up, eat and drink; for there is the sound of abundance of rain.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 18:42"},"So Ahab went up to eat and to drink. Ilyas went up to the top of Carmel; and he bowed himself down on the earth, and put\nhis face between his knees. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 18:43"},"He said to his servant, “Go up now, and look towards the sea.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He went up, and looked, and said, “There is nothing.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Go again” seven times. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"1KI 18:44"},"On the seventh time, he said, “Behold, a small cloud, like a man’s hand, is rising out of the sea.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Go up, tell Ahab, ‘Get ready and go down, so that the rain doesn’t stop you.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"1KI 18:45"},"In a little while, the sky grew black with clouds and wind, and there was a great rain. Ahab rode, and went to Jezreel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"1KI 18:46"},"The LORD’s hand was on Ilyas; and he tucked his cloak into his belt and ran before Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"1KI 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 19:1"},"Ahab told Jezebel all that Ilyas had done, and how he had killed all the prophets with the sword.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 19:2"},"Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Ilyas, saying, “So let the gods do to me, and more also, if I don’t make your life as the\nlife of one of them by tomorrow about this time!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 19:3"},"When he saw that, he arose, and ran for his life, and came to Beersheba, which belongs to Judah, and left his servant\nthere. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 19:4"},"But he himself went a day’s journey into the wilderness, and came and sat down under a juniper tree. Then he requested for\nhimself that he might die, and said, “It is enough. Now, O LORD, take away my life; for I am not better than my fathers.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 19:5"},"He lay down and slept under a juniper tree; and behold, an angel touched him, and said to him, “Arise and eat!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 19:6"},"He looked, and behold, there was at his head a cake baked on the coals, and a jar of water. He ate and drank, and lay down\nagain. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 19:7"},"The LORD’s angel came again the second time, and touched him, and said, “Arise and eat, because the journey is too great\nfor you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 19:8"},"He arose, and ate and drank, and went in the strength of that food forty days and forty nights to Horeb, Allah’s Mountain.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 19:9"},"He came to a cave there, and camped there; and behold, the LORD’s word came to him, and he said to him, “What are you\ndoing here, Ilyas?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 19:10"},"He said, “I have been very jealous for the LORD, Allah of Armies; for the children of Israel have forsaken your covenant,\nthrown down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword. I, even I only, am left; and they seek my life, to take it\naway.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 19:11"},"He said, “Go out, and stand on the mountain before the LORD.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Behold, the LORD passed by, and a great and strong wind tore the mountains, and broke in pieces the rocks before the LORD;\nbut the LORD was not in the wind. After the wind there was an earthquake; but the LORD was not in the earthquake.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 19:12"},"After the earthquake a fire passed; but the LORD was not in the fire. After the fire, there was a still small voice.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 19:13"},"When Ilyas heard it, he wrapped his face in his mantle, went out, and stood in the entrance of the cave. Behold, a voice\ncame to him, and said, “What are you doing here, Ilyas?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 19:14"},"He said, “I have been very jealous for the LORD, Allah of Armies; for the children of Israel have forsaken your covenant,\nthrown down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword. I, even I only, am left; and they seek my life, to take it\naway.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 19:15"},"The LORD said to him, “Go, return on your way to the wilderness of Damascus. When you arrive, anoint Hazael to be king\nover Syria. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 19:16"},"Anoint Jehu the son of Nimshi to be king over Israel; and anoint Alyas'a the son of Shaphat of Habil Meholah to be\nprophet in your place. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 19:17"},"He who escapes from the sword of Hazael, Jehu will kill; and he who escapes from the sword of Jehu, Alyas'a will kill.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 19:18"},"Yet I reserved seven thousand in Israel, all the knees of which have not bowed to Baal, and every mouth which has not\nkissed him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 19:19"},"So he departed from there, and found Alyas'a the son of Shaphat, who was ploughing with twelve yoke of oxen before him,\nand he with the twelfth. Ilyas went over to him, and put his mantle on him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 19:20"},"Alyas'a left the oxen, and ran after Ilyas, and said, “Let me please kiss my father and my mother, and then I will follow\nyou.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to him, “Go back again; for what have I done to you?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 19:21"},"He returned from following him, and took the yoke of oxen, and killed them, and boiled their meat with the instruments of\nthe oxen, and gave to the people, and they ate. Then he arose, and went after Ilyas, and served him.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"1KI 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 20:1"},"Ben Hadad the king of Syria gathered all his army together; and there were thirty-two kings with him, with horses and\nchariots. He went up and besieged Samaria, and fought against it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 20:2"},"He sent messengers to Ahab king of Israel, into the city, and said to him, “Ben Hadad says,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 20:3"},"‘Your silver and your gold is mine. Your wives also and your children, even the best, are mine.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 20:4"},"The king of Israel answered, “It is according to your saying, my lord, O king. I am yours, and all that I have.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 20:5"},"The messengers came again, and said, “Ben Hadad says, ‘I sent indeed to you, saying, “You shall deliver me your silver,\nand your gold, and your wives, and your children; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 20:6"},"but I will send my servants to you tomorrow about this time, and they will search your house, and the houses of your\nservants; whatever is pleasant in your eyes, they will put it in their hand, and take it away.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 20:7"},"Then the king of Israel called all the elders of the land, and said, “Please notice how this man seeks mischief; for he\nsent to me for my wives, and for my children, and for my silver, and for my gold; and I didn’t deny him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 20:8"},"All the elders and all the people said to him, “Don’t listen, and don’t consent.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 20:9"},"Therefore he said to the messengers of Ben Hadad, “Tell my lord the king, ‘All that you sent for to your servant at the\nfirst I will do; but this thing I cannot do.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The messengers departed, and brought him back the message. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 20:10"},"Ben Hadad sent to him, and said, “The gods do so to me, and more also, if the dust of Samaria will be enough for handfuls\nfor all the people who follow me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 20:11"},"The king of Israel answered, “Tell him, ‘Don’t let him who puts on his armour brag like he who takes it off.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 20:12"},"When Ben Hadad heard this message, as he was drinking, he and the kings, in the pavilions, he said to his servants,\n“Prepare to attack!” They prepared to attack the city. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 20:13"},"Behold, a prophet came near to Ahab king of Israel, and said, “The LORD says, ‘Have you seen all this great multitude?\nBehold, I will deliver it into your hand today. Then you will know that I am the LORD.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 20:14"},"Ahab said, “By whom?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “The LORD says, ‘By the young men of the princes of the provinces.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then he said, “Who shall begin the battle?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered, “You.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 20:15"},"Then he mustered the young men of the princes of the provinces, and they were two hundred and thirty-two. After them, he\nmustered all the people, even all the children of Israel, being seven thousand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 20:16"},"They went out at noon. But Ben Hadad was drinking himself drunk in the pavilions, he and the kings, the thirty-two kings\nwho helped him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 20:17"},"The young men of the princes of the provinces went out first; and Ben Hadad sent out, and they told him, saying, “Men are\ncoming out from Samaria.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 20:18"},"He said, “If they have come out for peace, take them alive; or if they have come out for war, take them alive.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 20:19"},"So these went out of the city, the young men of the princes of the provinces, and the army which followed them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 20:20"},"They each killed his man. The Syrians fled, and Israel pursued them. Ben Hadad the king of Syria escaped on a horse with\nhorsemen. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 20:21"},"The king of Israel went out, and struck the horses and chariots, and killed the Syrians with a great slaughter.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 20:22"},"The prophet came near to the king of Israel, and said to him, “Go, strengthen yourself, and mark, and see what you do;\nfor at the return of the year the king of Syria will come up against you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 20:23"},"The servants of the king of Syria said to him, “Their god is a god of the hills; therefore they were stronger than we.\nBut let’s fight against them in the plain, and surely we will be stronger than they.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 20:24"},"Do this thing: take the kings away, every man out of his place, and put captains in their place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 20:25"},"Muster an army, like the army that you have lost, horse for horse, and chariot for chariot. We will fight against them in\nthe plain, and surely we will be stronger than they are.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He listened to their voice, and did so. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 20:26"},"At the return of the year, Ben Hadad mustered the Syrians, and went up to Aphek, to fight against Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 20:27"},"The children of Israel were mustered and given provisions, and went against them. The children of Israel encamped before\nthem like two little flocks of young goats; but the Syrians filled the country.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 20:28"},"A man of Allah came near and spoke to the king of Israel, and said, “The LORD says, ‘Because the Syrians have said, “The\nLORD is a god of the hills, but he is not a god of the valleys;” therefore I will deliver all this great multitude into your\nhand, and you shall know that I am the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 20:29"},"They encamped opposite each other for seven days. So it was, that in the seventh day the battle was joined; and the\nchildren of Israel killed one hundred thousand footmen of the Syrians in one day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 20:30"},"But the rest fled to Aphek, into the city; and the wall fell on twenty-seven thousand men who were left. Ben Hadad fled,\nand came into the city, into an inner room. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 20:31"},"His servants said to him, “See now, we have heard that the kings of the house of Israel are merciful kings. Please let us\nput sackcloth on our bodies, and ropes on our heads, and go out to the king of Israel. Maybe he will save your life.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 20:32"},"So they put sackcloth on their bodies and ropes on their heads, and came to the king of Israel, and said, “Your servant\nBen Hadad says, ‘Please let me live.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Is he still alive? He is my brother.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 20:33"},"Now the men observed diligently, and hurried to take this phrase; and they said, “Your brother Ben Hadad.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then he said, “Go, bring him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Ben Hadad came out to him; and he caused him to come up into the chariot.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 20:34"},"Ben Hadad said to him, “The cities which my father took from your father I will restore. You shall make streets for\nyourself in Damascus, as my father made in Samaria.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I”, said Ahab, “will let you go with this covenant.” So he made a covenant with him, and let him go.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 20:35"},"A certain man of the sons of the prophets said to his fellow by the LORD’s word, “Please strike me!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The man refused to strike him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 20:36"},"Then he said to him, “Because you have not obeyed the LORD’s voice, behold, as soon as you have departed from me, a lion\nwill kill you.” As soon as he had departed from him, a lion found him and killed him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 20:37"},"Then he found another man, and said, “Please strike me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The man struck him and wounded him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 20:38"},"So the prophet departed, and waited for the king by the way, and disguised himself with his headband over his eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 20:39"},"As the king passed by, he cried to the king; and he said, “Your servant went out into the middle of the battle; and\nbehold, a man came over, and brought a man to me, and said, ‘Guard this man! If by any means he is missing, then your life\nshall be for his life, or else you shall pay a talent",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:39\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds"]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 20:40"},"As your servant was busy here and there, he was gone.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The king of Israel said to him, “So shall your judgement be. You yourself have decided it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 20:41"},"He hurried, and took the headband away from his eyes; and the king of Israel recognised that he was one of the prophets.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 20:42"},"He said to him, “The LORD says, ‘Because you have let go out of your hand the man whom I had devoted to destruction,\ntherefore your life will take the place of his life, and your people take the place of his people.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 20:43"},"The king of Israel went to his house sullen and angry, and came to Samaria.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"1KI 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 21:1"},"After these things, Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard, which was in Jezreel, next to the palace of Ahab king of\nSamaria. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 21:2"},"Ahab spoke to Naboth, saying, “Give me your vineyard, that I may have it for a garden of herbs, because it is near my\nhouse; and I will give you for it a better vineyard than it. Or, if it seems good to you, I will give you its worth in money.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 21:3"},"Naboth said to Ahab, “May the LORD forbid me, that I should give the inheritance of my fathers to you!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 21:4"},"Ahab came into his house sullen and angry because of the word which Naboth the Jezreelite had spoken to him; for he had\nsaid, “I will not give you the inheritance of my fathers.” He laid himself down on his bed, and turned away his face, and would\neat no bread. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 21:5"},"But Jezebel his wife came to him, and said to him, “Why is your spirit so sad, that you eat no bread?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 21:6"},"He said to her, “Because I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite, and said to him, ‘Give me your vineyard for money; or else, if\nit pleases you, I will give you another vineyard for it.’ He answered, ‘I will not give you my vineyard.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 21:7"},"Jezebel his wife said to him, “Do you now govern the kingdom of Israel? Arise, and eat bread, and let your heart be merry.\nI will give you the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 21:8"},"So she wrote letters in Ahab’s name, and sealed them with his seal, and sent the letters to the elders and to the nobles\nwho were in his city, who lived with Naboth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 21:9"},"She wrote in the letters, saying, “Proclaim a fast, and set Naboth on high amongst the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 21:10"},"Set two men, wicked fellows, before him, and let them testify against him, saying, ‘You cursed Allah and the king!’ Then\ncarry him out, and stone him to death.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 21:11"},"The men of his city, even the elders and the nobles who lived in his city, did as Jezebel had instructed them in the\nletters which she had written and sent to them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 21:12"},"They proclaimed a fast, and set Naboth on high amongst the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 21:13"},"The two men, the wicked fellows, came in and sat before him. The wicked fellows testified against him, even against\nNaboth, in the presence of the people, saying, “Naboth cursed Allah and the king!” Then they carried him out of the city and\nstoned him to death with stones. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 21:14"},"Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, “Naboth has been stoned, and is dead.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 21:15"},"When Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned, and was dead, Jezebel said to Ahab, “Arise, take possession of the\nvineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, which he refused to give you for money; for Naboth is not alive, but dead.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 21:16"},"When Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, Ahab rose up to go down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take\npossession of it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 21:17"},"The LORD’s word came to Ilyas the Tishbite, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 21:18"},"“Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who dwells in Samaria. Behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has\ngone down to take possession of it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 21:19"},"You shall speak to him, saying, ‘The LORD says, “Have you killed and also taken possession?”’ You shall speak to him,\nsaying, ‘The LORD says, “In the place where dogs licked the blood of Naboth, dogs will lick your blood, even yours.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 21:20"},"Ahab said to Ilyas, “Have you found me, my enemy?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered, “I have found you, because you have sold yourself to do that which is evil in the LORD’s sight.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 21:21"},"Behold, I will bring evil on you, and will utterly sweep you away and will cut off from Ahab everyone who urinates\nagainst a wall,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, male "]}],"caller":"+"}," and him who is shut up and him who is left at large in Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 21:22"},"I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah for\nthe provocation with which you have provoked me to anger, and have made Israel to sin.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 21:23"},"The LORD also spoke of Jezebel, saying, “The dogs will eat Jezebel by the rampart of Jezreel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 21:24"},"The dogs will eat he who dies of Ahab in the city; and the birds of the sky will eat he who dies in the field.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 21:25"},"But there was no one like Ahab, who sold himself to do that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, whom Jezebel his wife\nstirred up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 21:26"},"He did very abominably in following idols, according to all that the Amorites did, whom the LORD cast out before the\nchildren of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 21:27"},"When Ahab heard those words, he tore his clothes, and put sackcloth on his flesh, and fasted, and lay in sackcloth, and\nwent softly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 21:28"},"The LORD’s word came to Ilyas the Tishbite, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 21:29"},"“See how Ahab humbles himself before me? Because he humbles himself before me, I will not bring the evil in his days; but\nI will bring the evil on his house in his son’s day.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22","sid":"1KI 22"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"1KI 22:1"},"They continued three years without war between Syria and Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"1KI 22:2"},"In the third year, Jehoshaphat the king of Judah came down to the king of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"1KI 22:3"},"The king of Israel said to his servants, “You know that Ramoth Gilead is ours, and we do nothing, and don’t take it out of\nthe hand of the king of Syria?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"1KI 22:4"},"He said to Jehoshaphat, “Will you go with me to battle to Ramoth Gilead?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"1KI 22:5"},"Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “Please enquire first for the LORD’s word.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"1KI 22:6"},"Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four hundred men, and said to them, “Should I go against\nRamoth Gilead to battle, or should I refrain?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said, “Go up; for the Lord will deliver it into the hand of the king.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"1KI 22:7"},"But Jehoshaphat said, “Isn’t there here a prophet of the LORD, that we may enquire of him?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"1KI 22:8"},"The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “There is yet one man by whom we may enquire of the LORD, Micaiah the son of\nImlah; but I hate him, for he does not prophesy good concerning me, but evil.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jehoshaphat said, “Don’t let the king say so.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"1KI 22:9"},"Then the king of Israel called an officer, and said, “Quickly get Micaiah the son of Imlah.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"1KI 22:10"},"Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting each on his throne, arrayed in their robes, in an\nopen place at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets were prophesying before them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"1KI 22:11"},"Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made himself horns of iron, and said, “The LORD says, ‘With these you will push the\nSyrians, until they are consumed.’” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"1KI 22:12"},"All the prophets prophesied so, saying, “Go up to Ramoth Gilead, and prosper; for the LORD will deliver it into the hand\nof the king.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"1KI 22:13"},"The messenger who went to call Micaiah spoke to him, saying, “See now, the prophets declare good to the king with one\nmouth. Please let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak good.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"1KI 22:14"},"Micaiah said, “As the LORD lives, what the LORD says to me, that I will speak.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"1KI 22:15"},"When he had come to the king, the king said to him, “Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth Gilead to battle, or shall we\nforbear?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered him, “Go up and prosper; and the LORD will deliver it into the hand of the king.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"1KI 22:16"},"The king said to him, “How many times do I have to adjure you that you speak to me nothing but the truth in the LORD’s\nname?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"1KI 22:17"},"He said, “I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, as sheep that have no shepherd. The LORD said, ‘These have no\nmaster. Let them each return to his house in peace.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"1KI 22:18"},"The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “Didn’t I tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"1KI 22:19"},"Micaiah said, “Therefore hear the LORD’s word. I saw the LORD sitting on his throne, and all the army of heaven standing\nby him on his right hand and on his left. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"1KI 22:20"},"The LORD said, ‘Who will entice Ahab, that he may go up and fall at Ramoth Gilead?’ One said one thing; and another said\nanother. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"1KI 22:21"},"A spirit came out and stood before the LORD, and said, ‘I will entice him.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"1KI 22:22"},"The LORD said to him, ‘How?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, ‘I will go out and will be a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, ‘You will entice him, and will also prevail. Go out and do so.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"1KI 22:23"},"Now therefore, behold, the LORD has put a lying spirit in the mouth of all these your prophets; and the LORD has spoken\nevil concerning you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"1KI 22:24"},"Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near, and struck Micaiah on the cheek, and said, “Which way did the LORD’s Spirit\ngo from me to speak to you?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"1KI 22:25"},"Micaiah said, “Behold, you will see on that day, when you go into an inner room to hide yourself.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"1KI 22:26"},"The king of Israel said, “Take Micaiah, and carry him back to Amon the governor of the city, and to Joash the king’s son.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"1KI 22:27"},"Say, ‘The king says, “Put this fellow in the prison, and feed him with bread of affliction and with water of affliction,\nuntil I come in peace.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"1KI 22:28"},"Micaiah said, “If you return at all in peace, the LORD has not spoken by me.” He said, “Listen, all you people!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"1KI 22:29"},"So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to Ramoth Gilead.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"1KI 22:30"},"The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “I will disguise myself, and go into the battle; but you put on your robes.” The\nking of Israel disguised himself, and went into the battle. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"1KI 22:31"},"Now the king of Syria had commanded the thirty-two captains of his chariots, saying, “Don’t fight with small nor great,\nexcept only with the king of Israel.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"1KI 22:32"},"When the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, “Surely that is the king of Israel!” and they came over to\nfight against him. Jehoshaphat cried out. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"1KI 22:33"},"When the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"1KI 22:34"},"A certain man drew his bow at random, and struck the king of Israel between the joints of the armour. Therefore he said\nto the driver of his chariot, “Turn your hand, and carry me out of the battle; for I am severely wounded.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"1KI 22:35"},"The battle increased that day. The king was propped up in his chariot facing the Syrians, and died at evening. The blood\nran out of the wound into the bottom of the chariot. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"1KI 22:36"},"A cry went throughout the army about the going down of the sun, saying, “Every man to his city, and every man to his\ncountry!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"1KI 22:37"},"So the king died, and was brought to Samaria; and they buried the king in Samaria.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"1KI 22:38"},"They washed the chariot by the pool of Samaria; and the dogs licked up his blood where the prostitutes washed themselves;\naccording to the LORD’s word which he spoke. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"1KI 22:39"},"Now the rest of the acts of Ahab, and all that he did, and the ivory house which he built, and all the cities that he\nbuilt, aren’t they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"1KI 22:40"},"So Ahab slept with his fathers; and Ahaziah his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"1KI 22:41"},"Jehoshaphat the son of Asa began to reign over Judah in the fourth year of Ahab king of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"1KI 22:42"},"Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he began to reign; and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother’s\nname was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"1KI 22:43"},"He walked in all the way of Asa his father. He didn’t turn away from it, doing that which was right in the LORD’s eyes.\nHowever the high places were not taken away. The people still sacrificed and burnt incense on the high places.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"1KI 22:44"},"Jehoshaphat made peace with the king of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"1KI 22:45"},"Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, and his might that he showed, and how he fought, aren’t they written in the book\nof the chronicles of the kings of Judah? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"1KI 22:46"},"The remnant of the sodomites, that remained in the days of his father Asa, he put away out of the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"1KI 22:47"},"There was no king in Edom. A deputy ruled. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"1KI 22:48"},"Jehoshaphat made ships of Tarshish to go to Ophir for gold, but they didn’t go; for the ships wrecked at Ezion Geber.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"1KI 22:49"},"Then Ahaziah the son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, “Let my servants go with your servants in the ships.” But Jehoshaphat\nwould not. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"1KI 22:50"},"Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in his father Dawood’s city. Jehoram his son reigned\nin his place. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"1KI 22:51"},"Ahaziah the son of Ahab began to reign over Israel in Samaria in the seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and\nhe reigned two years over Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"1KI 22:52"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, and walked in the way of his father, and in the way of his mother, and in\nthe way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, in which he made Israel to sin.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"1KI 22:53"},"He served Baal and worshipped him, and provoked the LORD, Allah of Israel, to anger in all the ways that his father had\ndone so. "]}]}